1940 static struct pull_filter_list *
1941 alloc_pull_filter_list(struct options *o)
1942 {
1943  if (!o->pull_filter_list)
1944  {
1945  ALLOC_OBJ_CLEAR_GC(o->pull_filter_list, struct pull_filter_list, &o->gc);
1946  }
1947  return o->pull_filter_list;
1948 }
1949 
1950 static struct pull_filter *
1951 alloc_pull_filter(struct options *o, const int msglevel)
1952 {
1953  struct pull_filter_list *l = alloc_pull_filter_list(o);
1954  struct pull_filter *f;
1955 
1956  ALLOC_OBJ_CLEAR_GC(f, struct pull_filter, &o->gc);
1957  if (l->head)
1958  {
1959  ASSERT(l->tail);
1960  l->tail->next = f;
1961  }
1962  else
1963  {
1964  ASSERT(!l->tail);
1965  l->head = f;
1966  }
1967  l->tail = f;
1968  return f;
1969 }
1970 
1971 static void
1972 connection_entry_load_re(struct connection_entry *ce, const struct remote_entry *re)
1973 {
1974  if (re->remote)
1975  {
1976  ce->remote = re->remote;
1977  }
1978  if (re->remote_port)
1979  {
1980  ce->remote_port = re->remote_port;
1981  }
1982  if (re->proto >= 0)
1983  {
1984  ce->proto = re->proto;
1985  }
1986  if (re->af > 0)
1987  {
1988  ce->af = re->af;
1989  }
1990 }
1991 
1992 static void
1993 connection_entry_preload_key(const char **key_file, bool *key_inline,
1994  struct gc_arena *gc)
1995 {
1996  if (key_file && *key_file && !(*key_inline))
1997  {
1998  struct buffer in = buffer_read_from_file(*key_file, gc);
1999  if (!buf_valid(&in))
2000  {
2001  msg(M_FATAL, "Cannot pre-load keyfile (%s)", *key_file);
2002  }
2003 
2004  *key_file = (const char *) in.data;
2005  *key_inline = true;
2006  }
2007 }
2008 
2009 static void
2010 options_postprocess_verify_ce(const struct options *options,
2011  const struct connection_entry *ce)
2012 {
2013  struct options defaults;
2014  int dev = DEV_TYPE_UNDEF;
2015  bool pull = false;
2016 
2017  init_options(&defaults, true);
2018 
2019  if (options->test_crypto)
2020  {
2021  notnull(options->shared_secret_file, "key file (--secret)");
2022  }
2023  else
2024  {
2025  notnull(options->dev, "TUN/TAP device (--dev)");
2026  }
2027 
2028  /*
2029  * Get tun/tap/null device type
2030  */
2031  dev = dev_type_enum(options->dev, options->dev_type);
2032 
2033  /*
2034  * If "proto tcp" is specified, make sure we know whether it is
2035  * tcp-client or tcp-server.
2036  */
2037  if (ce->proto == PROTO_TCP)
2038  {
2039  msg(M_USAGE,
2040  "--proto tcp is ambiguous in this context. Please specify "
2041  "--proto tcp-server or --proto tcp-client");
2042  }
2043 
2044  /*
2045  * Sanity check on daemon/inetd modes
2046  */
2047 
2048  if (options->daemon && options->inetd)
2049  {
2050  msg(M_USAGE, "only one of --daemon or --inetd may be specified");
2051  }
2052 
2053  if (options->inetd && (ce->local || ce->remote))
2054  {
2055  msg(M_USAGE, "--local or --remote cannot be used with --inetd");
2056  }
2057 
2058  if (options->inetd && ce->proto == PROTO_TCP_CLIENT)
2059  {
2060  msg(M_USAGE, "--proto tcp-client cannot be used with --inetd");
2061  }
2062 
2063  if (options->inetd == INETD_NOWAIT && ce->proto != PROTO_TCP_SERVER)
2064  {
2065  msg(M_USAGE, "--inetd nowait can only be used with --proto tcp-server");
2066  }
2067 
2068  if (options->inetd == INETD_NOWAIT
2069  && !(options->tls_server || options->tls_client))
2070  {
2071  msg(M_USAGE, "--inetd nowait can only be used in TLS mode");
2072  }
2073 
2074  if (options->inetd == INETD_NOWAIT && dev != DEV_TYPE_TAP)
2075  {
2076  msg(M_USAGE, "--inetd nowait only makes sense in --dev tap mode");
2077  }
2078 
2079  if (options->inetd)
2080  {
2081  msg(M_WARN,
2082  "DEPRECATED OPTION: --inetd mode is deprecated and will be removed "
2083  "in OpenVPN 2.6");
2084  }
2085 
2086  if (options->lladdr && dev != DEV_TYPE_TAP)
2087  {
2088  msg(M_USAGE, "--lladdr can only be used in --dev tap mode");
2089  }
2090 
2091  /*
2092  * Sanity check on MTU parameters
2093  */
2094  if (options->ce.tun_mtu_defined && options->ce.link_mtu_defined)
2095  {
2096  msg(M_USAGE,
2097  "only one of --tun-mtu or --link-mtu may be defined (note that "
2098  "--ifconfig implies --link-mtu %d)", LINK_MTU_DEFAULT);
2099  }
2100 
2101  if (!proto_is_udp(ce->proto) && options->mtu_test)
2102  {
2103  msg(M_USAGE, "--mtu-test only makes sense with --proto udp");
2104  }
2105 
2106  /* will we be pulling options from server? */
2107 #if P2MP
2108  pull = options->pull;
2109 #endif
2110 
2111  /*
2112  * Sanity check on --local, --remote, and --ifconfig
2113  */
2114 
2115  if (proto_is_net(ce->proto)
2116  && string_defined_equal(ce->local, ce->remote)
2117  && string_defined_equal(ce->local_port, ce->remote_port))
2118  {
2119  msg(M_USAGE, "--remote and --local addresses are the same");
2120  }
2121 
2122  if (string_defined_equal(ce->remote, options->ifconfig_local)
2123  || string_defined_equal(ce->remote, options->ifconfig_remote_netmask))
2124  {
2125  msg(M_USAGE,
2126  "--local and --remote addresses must be distinct from --ifconfig "
2127  "addresses");
2128  }
2129 
2130  if (string_defined_equal(ce->local, options->ifconfig_local)
2131  || string_defined_equal(ce->local, options->ifconfig_remote_netmask))
2132  {
2133  msg(M_USAGE,
2134  "--local addresses must be distinct from --ifconfig addresses");
2135  }
2136 
2137  if (string_defined_equal(options->ifconfig_local,
2138  options->ifconfig_remote_netmask))
2139  {
2140  msg(M_USAGE,
2141  "local and remote/netmask --ifconfig addresses must be different");
2142  }
2143 
2144  if (ce->bind_defined && !ce->bind_local)
2145  {
2146  msg(M_USAGE, "--bind and --nobind can't be used together");
2147  }
2148 
2149  if (ce->local && !ce->bind_local)
2150  {
2151  msg(M_USAGE,
2152  "--local and --nobind don't make sense when used together");
2153  }
2154 
2155  if (ce->local_port_defined && !ce->bind_local)
2156  {
2157  msg(M_USAGE,
2158  "--lport and --nobind don't make sense when used together");
2159  }
2160 
2161  if (!ce->remote && !ce->bind_local)
2162  {
2163  msg(M_USAGE, "--nobind doesn't make sense unless used with --remote");
2164  }
2165 
2166  /*
2167  * Check for consistency of management options
2168  */
2169 #ifdef ENABLE_MANAGEMENT
2170  if (!options->management_addr
2171  && (options->management_flags
2172  || options->management_write_peer_info_file
2173  || options->management_log_history_cache != defaults.management_log_history_cache))
2174  {
2175  msg(M_USAGE, "--management is not specified, however one or more options which modify the behavior of --management were specified");
2176  }
2177 
2178  if ((options->management_client_user || options->management_client_group)
2179  && !(options->management_flags & MF_UNIX_SOCK))
2180  {
2181  msg(M_USAGE, "--management-client-(user|group) can only be used on unix domain sockets");
2182  }
2183 
2184  if (options->management_addr
2185  && !(options->management_flags & MF_UNIX_SOCK)
2186  && (!options->management_user_pass))
2187  {
2188  msg(M_WARN, "WARNING: Using --management on a TCP port WITHOUT "
2189  "passwords is STRONGLY discouraged and considered insecure");
2190  }
2191 
2192 #endif /* ifdef ENABLE_MANAGEMENT */
2193 
2194 #if defined(ENABLE_MANAGEMENT)
2195  if ((tls_version_max() >= TLS_VER_1_3)
2196  && (options->management_flags & MF_EXTERNAL_KEY)
2197  && !(options->management_flags & (MF_EXTERNAL_KEY_NOPADDING))
2198  )
2199  {
2200  msg(M_ERR, "management-external-key with OpenSSL 1.1.1 requires "
2201  "the nopadding argument/support");
2202  }
2203 #endif
2204  /*
2205  * Windows-specific options.
2206  */
2207 
2208 #ifdef _WIN32
2209  if (dev == DEV_TYPE_TUN && !(pull || (options->ifconfig_local && options->ifconfig_remote_netmask)))
2210  {
2211  msg(M_USAGE, "On Windows, --ifconfig is required when --dev tun is used");
2212  }
2213 
2214  if ((options->tuntap_options.ip_win32_defined)
2215  && !(pull || (options->ifconfig_local && options->ifconfig_remote_netmask)))
2216  {
2217  msg(M_USAGE, "On Windows, --ip-win32 doesn't make sense unless --ifconfig is also used");
2218  }
2219 
2220  if (options->tuntap_options.dhcp_options
2221  && options->windows_driver != WINDOWS_DRIVER_WINTUN
2222  && options->tuntap_options.ip_win32_type != IPW32_SET_DHCP_MASQ
2223  && options->tuntap_options.ip_win32_type != IPW32_SET_ADAPTIVE)
2224  {
2225  msg(M_USAGE, "--dhcp-option requires --ip-win32 dynamic or adaptive");
2226  }
2227 
2228  if (options->windows_driver == WINDOWS_DRIVER_WINTUN && dev != DEV_TYPE_TUN)
2229  {
2230  msg(M_USAGE, "--windows-driver wintun requires --dev tun");
2231  }
2232 #endif /* ifdef _WIN32 */
2233 
2234  /*
2235  * Check that protocol options make sense.
2236  */
2237 
2238 #ifdef ENABLE_FRAGMENT
2239  if (!proto_is_udp(ce->proto) && ce->fragment)
2240  {
2241  msg(M_USAGE, "--fragment can only be used with --proto udp");
2242  }
2243 #endif
2244 
2245  if (!proto_is_udp(ce->proto) && ce->explicit_exit_notification)
2246  {
2247  msg(M_USAGE,
2248  "--explicit-exit-notify can only be used with --proto udp");
2249  }
2250 
2251  if (!ce->remote && ce->proto == PROTO_TCP_CLIENT)
2252  {
2253  msg(M_USAGE, "--remote MUST be used in TCP Client mode");
2254  }
2255 
2256  if ((ce->http_proxy_options) && ce->proto != PROTO_TCP_CLIENT)
2257  {
2258  msg(M_USAGE,
2259  "--http-proxy MUST be used in TCP Client mode (i.e. --proto "
2260  "tcp-client)");
2261  }
2262 
2263  if ((ce->http_proxy_options) && !ce->http_proxy_options->server)
2264  {
2265  msg(M_USAGE,
2266  "--http-proxy not specified but other http proxy options present");
2267  }
2268 
2269  if (ce->http_proxy_options && ce->socks_proxy_server)
2270  {
2271  msg(M_USAGE,
2272  "--http-proxy can not be used together with --socks-proxy");
2273  }
2274 
2275  if (ce->socks_proxy_server && ce->proto == PROTO_TCP_SERVER)
2276  {
2277  msg(M_USAGE, "--socks-proxy can not be used in TCP Server mode");
2278  }
2279 
2280  if (ce->proto == PROTO_TCP_SERVER && (options->connection_list->len > 1))
2281  {
2282  msg(M_USAGE, "TCP server mode allows at most one --remote address");
2283  }
2284 
2285  /*
2286  * Check consistency of --mode server options.
2287  */
2288  if (options->mode == MODE_SERVER)
2289  {
2290 #define USAGE_VALID_SERVER_PROTOS "--mode server currently only supports " \
2291  "--proto values of udp, tcp-server, tcp4-server, or tcp6-server"
2292 #ifdef TARGET_ANDROID
2293  msg(M_FATAL, "--mode server not supported on Android");
2294 #endif
2295  if (!(dev == DEV_TYPE_TUN || dev == DEV_TYPE_TAP))
2296  {
2297  msg(M_USAGE, "--mode server only works with --dev tun or --dev tap");
2298  }
2299  if (options->pull)
2300  {
2301  msg(M_USAGE, "--pull cannot be used with --mode server");
2302  }
2303  if (options->pull_filter_list)
2304  {
2305  msg(M_WARN, "--pull-filter ignored for --mode server");
2306  }
2307  if (!(proto_is_udp(ce->proto) || ce->proto == PROTO_TCP_SERVER))
2308  {
2309  msg(M_USAGE, USAGE_VALID_SERVER_PROTOS);
2310  }
2311 #if PORT_SHARE
2312  if ((options->port_share_host || options->port_share_port)
2313  && (ce->proto != PROTO_TCP_SERVER))
2314  {
2315  msg(M_USAGE, "--port-share only works in TCP server mode "
2316  "(--proto values of tcp-server, tcp4-server, or tcp6-server)");
2317  }
2318 #endif
2319  if (!options->tls_server)
2320  {
2321  msg(M_USAGE, "--mode server requires --tls-server");
2322  }
2323  if (ce->remote)
2324  {
2325  msg(M_USAGE, "--remote cannot be used with --mode server");
2326  }
2327  if (!ce->bind_local)
2328  {
2329  msg(M_USAGE, "--nobind cannot be used with --mode server");
2330  }
2331  if (ce->http_proxy_options)
2332  {
2333  msg(M_USAGE, "--http-proxy cannot be used with --mode server");
2334  }
2335  if (ce->socks_proxy_server)
2336  {
2337  msg(M_USAGE, "--socks-proxy cannot be used with --mode server");
2338  }
2339  /* <connection> blocks force to have a remote embedded, so we check
2340  * for the --remote and bail out if it is present
2341  */
2342  if (options->connection_list->len >1
2343  || options->connection_list->array[0]->remote)
2344  {
2345  msg(M_USAGE, "<connection> cannot be used with --mode server");
2346  }
2347 
2348  if (options->shaper)
2349  {
2350  msg(M_USAGE, "--shaper cannot be used with --mode server");
2351  }
2352  if (options->inetd)
2353  {
2354  msg(M_USAGE, "--inetd cannot be used with --mode server");
2355  }
2356  if (options->ipchange)
2357  {
2358  msg(M_USAGE,
2359  "--ipchange cannot be used with --mode server (use "
2360  "--client-connect instead)");
2361  }
2362  if (!(proto_is_dgram(ce->proto) || ce->proto == PROTO_TCP_SERVER))
2363  {
2364  msg(M_USAGE, USAGE_VALID_SERVER_PROTOS);
2365  }
2366  if (!proto_is_udp(ce->proto) && (options->cf_max || options->cf_per))
2367  {
2368  msg(M_USAGE, "--connect-freq only works with --mode server --proto udp. Try --max-clients instead.");
2369  }
2370  if (!(dev == DEV_TYPE_TAP || (dev == DEV_TYPE_TUN && options->topology == TOP_SUBNET)) && options->ifconfig_pool_netmask)
2371  {
2372  msg(M_USAGE, "The third parameter to --ifconfig-pool (netmask) is only valid in --dev tap mode");
2373  }
2374  if (options->routes && (options->routes->flags & RG_ENABLE))
2375  {
2376  msg(M_USAGE, "--redirect-gateway cannot be used with --mode server (however --push \"redirect-gateway\" is fine)");
2377  }
2378  if (options->route_delay_defined)
2379  {
2380  msg(M_USAGE, "--route-delay cannot be used with --mode server");
2381  }
2382  if (options->up_delay)
2383  {
2384  msg(M_USAGE, "--up-delay cannot be used with --mode server");
2385  }
2386  if (!options->ifconfig_pool_defined
2387  && !options->ifconfig_ipv6_pool_defined
2388  && options->ifconfig_pool_persist_filename)
2389  {
2390  msg(M_USAGE,
2391  "--ifconfig-pool-persist must be used with --ifconfig-pool or --ifconfig-ipv6-pool");
2392  }
2393  if (options->ifconfig_ipv6_pool_defined && !options->ifconfig_ipv6_local)
2394  {
2395  msg(M_USAGE, "--ifconfig-ipv6-pool needs --ifconfig-ipv6");
2396  }
2397  if (options->allow_recursive_routing)
2398  {
2399  msg(M_USAGE, "--allow-recursive-routing cannot be used with --mode server");
2400  }
2401  if (options->auth_user_pass_file)
2402  {
2403  msg(M_USAGE, "--auth-user-pass cannot be used with --mode server (it should be used on the client side only)");
2404  }
2405  if (options->ccd_exclusive && !options->client_config_dir)
2406  {
2407  msg(M_USAGE, "--ccd-exclusive must be used with --client-config-dir");
2408  }
2409  if (options->auth_token_generate && !options->renegotiate_seconds)
2410  {
2411  msg(M_USAGE, "--auth-gen-token needs a non-infinite "
2412  "--renegotiate_seconds setting");
2413  }
2414  {
2415  const bool ccnr = (options->auth_user_pass_verify_script
2416  || PLUGIN_OPTION_LIST(options)
2417  || MAN_CLIENT_AUTH_ENABLED(options));
2418  const char *postfix = "must be used with --management-client-auth, an --auth-user-pass-verify script, or plugin";
2419  if ((options->ssl_flags & (SSLF_CLIENT_CERT_NOT_REQUIRED|SSLF_CLIENT_CERT_OPTIONAL)) && !ccnr)
2420  {
2421  msg(M_USAGE, "--verify-client-cert none|optional %s", postfix);
2422  }
2423  if ((options->ssl_flags & SSLF_USERNAME_AS_COMMON_NAME) && !ccnr)
2424  {
2425  msg(M_USAGE, "--username-as-common-name %s", postfix);
2426  }
2427  if ((options->ssl_flags & SSLF_AUTH_USER_PASS_OPTIONAL) && !ccnr)
2428  {
2429  msg(M_USAGE, "--auth-user-pass-optional %s", postfix);
2430  }
2431  }
2432 
2433  if (options->vlan_tagging && dev != DEV_TYPE_TAP)
2434  {
2435  msg(M_USAGE, "--vlan-tagging must be used with --dev tap");
2436  }
2437  if (!options->vlan_tagging)
2438  {
2439  if (options->vlan_accept != defaults.vlan_accept)
2440  {
2441  msg(M_USAGE, "--vlan-accept requires --vlan-tagging");
2442  }
2443  if (options->vlan_pvid != defaults.vlan_pvid)
2444  {
2445  msg(M_USAGE, "--vlan-pvid requires --vlan-tagging");
2446  }
2447  }
2448  }
2449  else
2450  {
2451  /*
2452  * When not in server mode, err if parameters are
2453  * specified which require --mode server.
2454  */
2455  if (options->ifconfig_pool_defined || options->ifconfig_pool_persist_filename)
2456  {
2457  msg(M_USAGE, "--ifconfig-pool/--ifconfig-pool-persist requires --mode server");
2458  }
2459  if (options->ifconfig_ipv6_pool_defined)
2460  {
2461  msg(M_USAGE, "--ifconfig-ipv6-pool requires --mode server");
2462  }
2463  if (options->real_hash_size != defaults.real_hash_size
2464  || options->virtual_hash_size != defaults.virtual_hash_size)
2465  {
2466  msg(M_USAGE, "--hash-size requires --mode server");
2467  }
2468  if (options->learn_address_script)
2469  {
2470  msg(M_USAGE, "--learn-address requires --mode server");
2471  }
2472  if (options->client_connect_script)
2473  {
2474  msg(M_USAGE, "--client-connect requires --mode server");
2475  }
2476  if (options->client_disconnect_script)
2477  {
2478  msg(M_USAGE, "--client-disconnect requires --mode server");
2479  }
2480  if (options->client_config_dir || options->ccd_exclusive)
2481  {
2482  msg(M_USAGE, "--client-config-dir/--ccd-exclusive requires --mode server");
2483  }
2484  if (options->enable_c2c)
2485  {
2486  msg(M_USAGE, "--client-to-client requires --mode server");
2487  }
2488  if (options->duplicate_cn)
2489  {
2490  msg(M_USAGE, "--duplicate-cn requires --mode server");
2491  }
2492  if (options->cf_max || options->cf_per)
2493  {
2494  msg(M_USAGE, "--connect-freq requires --mode server");
2495  }
2496  if (options->ssl_flags & (SSLF_CLIENT_CERT_NOT_REQUIRED|SSLF_CLIENT_CERT_OPTIONAL))
2497  {
2498  msg(M_USAGE, "--verify-client-cert requires --mode server");
2499  }
2500  if (options->ssl_flags & SSLF_USERNAME_AS_COMMON_NAME)
2501  {
2502  msg(M_USAGE, "--username-as-common-name requires --mode server");
2503  }
2504  if (options->ssl_flags & SSLF_AUTH_USER_PASS_OPTIONAL)
2505  {
2506  msg(M_USAGE, "--auth-user-pass-optional requires --mode server");
2507  }
2508  if (options->ssl_flags & SSLF_OPT_VERIFY)
2509  {
2510  msg(M_USAGE, "--opt-verify requires --mode server");
2511  }
2512  if (options->server_flags & SF_TCP_NODELAY_HELPER)
2513  {
2514  msg(M_WARN, "WARNING: setting tcp-nodelay on the client side will not "
2515  "affect the server. To have TCP_NODELAY in both direction use "
2516  "tcp-nodelay in the server configuration instead.");
2517  }
2518  if (options->auth_user_pass_verify_script)
2519  {
2520  msg(M_USAGE, "--auth-user-pass-verify requires --mode server");
2521  }
2522  if (options->auth_token_generate)
2523  {
2524  msg(M_USAGE, "--auth-gen-token requires --mode server");
2525  }
2526 #if PORT_SHARE
2527  if (options->port_share_host || options->port_share_port)
2528  {
2529  msg(M_USAGE, "--port-share requires TCP server mode (--mode server --proto tcp-server)");
2530  }
2531 #endif
2532 
2533  if (options->stale_routes_check_interval)
2534  {
2535  msg(M_USAGE, "--stale-routes-check requires --mode server");
2536  }
2537 
2538  if (options->vlan_tagging)
2539  {
2540  msg(M_USAGE, "--vlan-tagging requires --mode server");
2541  }
2542  }
2543 
2544  if (options->keysize)
2545  {
2546  msg(M_WARN, "WARNING: --keysize is DEPRECATED and will be removed in OpenVPN 2.6");
2547  }
2548 
2549  /*
2550  * Check consistency of replay options
2551  */
2552  if (!options->replay
2553  && (options->replay_window != defaults.replay_window
2554  || options->replay_time != defaults.replay_time))
2555  {
2556  msg(M_USAGE, "--replay-window doesn't make sense when replay protection is disabled with --no-replay");
2557  }
2558 
2559  /*
2560  * SSL/TLS mode sanity checks.
2561  */
2562  if (options->tls_server + options->tls_client
2563  +(options->shared_secret_file != NULL) > 1)
2564  {
2565  msg(M_USAGE, "specify only one of --tls-server, --tls-client, or --secret");
2566  }
2567 
2568  if (options->ssl_flags & (SSLF_CLIENT_CERT_NOT_REQUIRED|SSLF_CLIENT_CERT_OPTIONAL))
2569  {
2570  msg(M_WARN, "WARNING: POTENTIALLY DANGEROUS OPTION "
2571  "--verify-client-cert none|optional "
2572  "may accept clients which do not present a certificate");
2573  }
2574 
2575  const int tls_version_max =
2576  (options->ssl_flags >> SSLF_TLS_VERSION_MAX_SHIFT)
2577  & SSLF_TLS_VERSION_MAX_MASK;
2578  const int tls_version_min =
2579  (options->ssl_flags >> SSLF_TLS_VERSION_MIN_SHIFT)
2580  & SSLF_TLS_VERSION_MIN_MASK;
2581 
2582  if (tls_version_max > 0 && tls_version_max < tls_version_min)
2583  {
2584  msg(M_USAGE, "--tls-version-min bigger than --tls-version-max");
2585  }
2586 
2587  if (options->tls_server || options->tls_client)
2588  {
2589 #ifdef ENABLE_PKCS11
2590  if (options->pkcs11_providers[0])
2591  {
2592  notnull(options->ca_file, "CA file (--ca)");
2593 
2594  if (options->pkcs11_id_management && options->pkcs11_id != NULL)
2595  {
2596  msg(M_USAGE, "Parameter --pkcs11-id cannot be used when --pkcs11-id-management is also specified.");
2597  }
2598  if (!options->pkcs11_id_management && options->pkcs11_id == NULL)
2599  {
2600  msg(M_USAGE, "Parameter --pkcs11-id or --pkcs11-id-management should be specified.");
2601  }
2602  if (options->cert_file)
2603  {
2604  msg(M_USAGE, "Parameter --cert cannot be used when --pkcs11-provider is also specified.");
2605  }
2606  if (options->priv_key_file)
2607  {
2608  msg(M_USAGE, "Parameter --key cannot be used when --pkcs11-provider is also specified.");
2609  }
2610 #ifdef ENABLE_MANAGEMENT
2611  if (options->management_flags & MF_EXTERNAL_KEY)
2612  {
2613  msg(M_USAGE, "Parameter --management-external-key cannot be used when --pkcs11-provider is also specified.");
2614  }
2615  if (options->management_flags & MF_EXTERNAL_CERT)
2616  {
2617  msg(M_USAGE, "Parameter --management-external-cert cannot be used when --pkcs11-provider is also specified.");
2618  }
2619 #endif
2620  if (options->pkcs12_file)
2621  {
2622  msg(M_USAGE, "Parameter --pkcs12 cannot be used when --pkcs11-provider is also specified.");
2623  }
2624 #ifdef ENABLE_CRYPTOAPI
2625  if (options->cryptoapi_cert)
2626  {
2627  msg(M_USAGE, "Parameter --cryptoapicert cannot be used when --pkcs11-provider is also specified.");
2628  }
2629 #endif
2630  }
2631  else
2632 #endif /* ifdef ENABLE_PKCS11 */
2633 #ifdef ENABLE_MANAGEMENT
2634  if ((options->management_flags & MF_EXTERNAL_KEY) && options->priv_key_file)
2635  {
2636  msg(M_USAGE, "--key and --management-external-key are mutually exclusive");
2637  }
2638  else if ((options->management_flags & MF_EXTERNAL_CERT))
2639  {
2640  if (options->cert_file)
2641  {
2642  msg(M_USAGE, "--cert and --management-external-cert are mutually exclusive");
2643  }
2644  else if (!(options->management_flags & MF_EXTERNAL_KEY))
2645  {
2646  msg(M_USAGE, "--management-external-cert must be used with --management-external-key");
2647  }
2648  }
2649  else
2650 #endif
2651 #ifdef ENABLE_CRYPTOAPI
2652  if (options->cryptoapi_cert)
2653  {
2654  if ((!(options->ca_file)) && (!(options->ca_path)))
2655  {
2656  msg(M_USAGE, "You must define CA file (--ca) or CA path (--capath)");
2657  }
2658  if (options->cert_file)
2659  {
2660  msg(M_USAGE, "Parameter --cert cannot be used when --cryptoapicert is also specified.");
2661  }
2662  if (options->priv_key_file)
2663  {
2664  msg(M_USAGE, "Parameter --key cannot be used when --cryptoapicert is also specified.");
2665  }
2666  if (options->pkcs12_file)
2667  {
2668  msg(M_USAGE, "Parameter --pkcs12 cannot be used when --cryptoapicert is also specified.");
2669  }
2670 #ifdef ENABLE_MANAGEMENT
2671  if (options->management_flags & MF_EXTERNAL_KEY)
2672  {
2673  msg(M_USAGE, "Parameter --management-external-key cannot be used when --cryptoapicert is also specified.");
2674  }
2675  if (options->management_flags & MF_EXTERNAL_CERT)
2676  {
2677  msg(M_USAGE, "Parameter --management-external-cert cannot be used when --cryptoapicert is also specified.");
2678  }
2679 #endif
2680  }
2681  else
2682 #endif /* ifdef ENABLE_CRYPTOAPI */
2683  if (options->pkcs12_file)
2684  {
2685 #ifdef ENABLE_CRYPTO_MBEDTLS
2686  msg(M_USAGE, "Parameter --pkcs12 cannot be used with the mbed TLS version version of OpenVPN.");
2687 #else
2688  if (options->ca_path)
2689  {
2690  msg(M_USAGE, "Parameter --capath cannot be used when --pkcs12 is also specified.");
2691  }
2692  if (options->cert_file)
2693  {
2694  msg(M_USAGE, "Parameter --cert cannot be used when --pkcs12 is also specified.");
2695  }
2696  if (options->priv_key_file)
2697  {
2698  msg(M_USAGE, "Parameter --key cannot be used when --pkcs12 is also specified.");
2699  }
2700 #ifdef ENABLE_MANAGEMENT
2701  if (options->management_flags & MF_EXTERNAL_KEY)
2702  {
2703  msg(M_USAGE, "Parameter --management-external-key cannot be used when --pkcs12 is also specified.");
2704  }
2705  if (options->management_flags & MF_EXTERNAL_CERT)
2706  {
2707  msg(M_USAGE, "Parameter --management-external-cert cannot be used when --pkcs12 is also specified.");
2708  }
2709 #endif
2710 #endif /* ifdef ENABLE_CRYPTO_MBEDTLS */
2711  }
2712  else
2713  {
2714 #ifdef ENABLE_CRYPTO_MBEDTLS
2715  if (!(options->ca_file))
2716  {
2717  msg(M_USAGE, "You must define CA file (--ca)");
2718  }
2719  if (options->ca_path)
2720  {
2721  msg(M_USAGE, "Parameter --capath cannot be used with the mbed TLS version version of OpenVPN.");
2722  }
2723 #else /* ifdef ENABLE_CRYPTO_MBEDTLS */
2724  if ((!(options->ca_file)) && (!(options->ca_path)))
2725  {
2726  msg(M_USAGE, "You must define CA file (--ca) or CA path (--capath)");
2727  }
2728 #endif
2729  if (pull)
2730  {
2731 
2732  const int sum =
2733 #ifdef ENABLE_MANAGEMENT
2734  ((options->cert_file != NULL) || (options->management_flags & MF_EXTERNAL_CERT))
2735  +((options->priv_key_file != NULL) || (options->management_flags & MF_EXTERNAL_KEY));
2736 #else
2737  (options->cert_file != NULL) + (options->priv_key_file != NULL);
2738 #endif
2739 
2740  if (sum == 0)
2741  {
2742 #if P2MP
2743  if (!options->auth_user_pass_file)
2744 #endif
2745  msg(M_USAGE, "No client-side authentication method is specified. You must use either --cert/--key, --pkcs12, or --auth-user-pass");
2746  }
2747  else if (sum == 2)
2748  {
2749  }
2750  else
2751  {
2752  msg(M_USAGE, "If you use one of --cert or --key, you must use them both");
2753  }
2754  }
2755  else
2756  {
2757 #ifdef ENABLE_MANAGEMENT
2758  if (!(options->management_flags & MF_EXTERNAL_CERT))
2759 #endif
2760  notnull(options->cert_file, "certificate file (--cert) or PKCS#12 file (--pkcs12)");
2761 #ifdef ENABLE_MANAGEMENT
2762  if (!(options->management_flags & MF_EXTERNAL_KEY))
2763 #endif
2764  notnull(options->priv_key_file, "private key file (--key) or PKCS#12 file (--pkcs12)");
2765  }
2766  }
2767  if (ce->tls_auth_file && ce->tls_crypt_file)
2768  {
2769  msg(M_USAGE, "--tls-auth and --tls-crypt are mutually exclusive");
2770  }
2771  if (options->tls_client && ce->tls_crypt_v2_file
2772  && (ce->tls_auth_file || ce->tls_crypt_file))
2773  {
2774  msg(M_USAGE, "--tls-crypt-v2, --tls-auth and --tls-crypt are mutually exclusive in client mode");
2775  }
2776  }
2777  else
2778  {
2779  /*
2780  * Make sure user doesn't specify any TLS options
2781  * when in non-TLS mode.
2782  */
2783 
2784 #define MUST_BE_UNDEF(parm) if (options->parm != defaults.parm) {msg(M_USAGE, err, #parm); \
2785 }
2786 
2787  const char err[] = "Parameter %s can only be specified in TLS-mode, i.e. where --tls-server or --tls-client is also specified.";
2788 
2789  MUST_BE_UNDEF(ca_file);
2790  MUST_BE_UNDEF(ca_path);
2791  MUST_BE_UNDEF(dh_file);
2792  MUST_BE_UNDEF(cert_file);
2793  MUST_BE_UNDEF(priv_key_file);
2794 #ifndef ENABLE_CRYPTO_MBEDTLS
2795  MUST_BE_UNDEF(pkcs12_file);
2796 #endif
2797  MUST_BE_UNDEF(cipher_list);
2798  MUST_BE_UNDEF(cipher_list_tls13);
2799  MUST_BE_UNDEF(tls_cert_profile);
2800  MUST_BE_UNDEF(tls_verify);
2801  MUST_BE_UNDEF(tls_export_cert);
2802  MUST_BE_UNDEF(verify_x509_name);
2803  MUST_BE_UNDEF(tls_timeout);
2804  MUST_BE_UNDEF(renegotiate_bytes);
2805  MUST_BE_UNDEF(renegotiate_packets);
2806  MUST_BE_UNDEF(renegotiate_seconds);
2807  MUST_BE_UNDEF(handshake_window);
2808  MUST_BE_UNDEF(transition_window);
2809  MUST_BE_UNDEF(tls_auth_file);
2810  MUST_BE_UNDEF(tls_crypt_file);
2811  MUST_BE_UNDEF(tls_crypt_v2_file);
2812  MUST_BE_UNDEF(single_session);
2813  MUST_BE_UNDEF(push_peer_info);
2814  MUST_BE_UNDEF(tls_exit);
2815  MUST_BE_UNDEF(crl_file);
2816  MUST_BE_UNDEF(ns_cert_type);
2817  MUST_BE_UNDEF(remote_cert_ku[0]);
2818  MUST_BE_UNDEF(remote_cert_eku);
2819 #ifdef ENABLE_PKCS11

2821  MUST_BE_UNDEF(pkcs11_private_mode[0]);
2822  MUST_BE_UNDEF(pkcs11_id);
2823  MUST_BE_UNDEF(pkcs11_id_management);
2824 #endif
2825 
2826  if (pull)
2827  {
2828  msg(M_USAGE, err, "--pull");
2829  }
2830  }
2831 #undef MUST_BE_UNDEF
2832 
2833 #if P2MP
2834  if (options->auth_user_pass_file && !options->pull)
2835  {
2836  msg(M_USAGE, "--auth-user-pass requires --pull");
2837  }
2838 #endif
2839 
2840  uninit_options(&defaults);
2841 }
2842 
2843 static void
2844 options_postprocess_mutate_ce(struct options *o, struct connection_entry *ce)
2845 {
2846  const int dev = dev_type_enum(o->dev, o->dev_type);
2847 
2848  if (o->server_defined || o->server_bridge_defined || o->server_bridge_proxy_dhcp)
2849  {
2850  if (ce->proto == PROTO_TCP)
2851  {
2852  ce->proto = PROTO_TCP_SERVER;
2853  }
2854  }
2855 
2856 #if P2MP
2857  if (o->client)
2858  {
2859  if (ce->proto == PROTO_TCP)
2860  {
2861  ce->proto = PROTO_TCP_CLIENT;
2862  }
2863  }
2864 #endif
2865 
2866  if (ce->proto == PROTO_TCP_CLIENT && !ce->local
2867  && !ce->local_port_defined && !ce->bind_defined)
2868  {
2869  ce->bind_local = false;
2870  }
2871 
2872  if (ce->proto == PROTO_UDP && ce->socks_proxy_server && !ce->local
2873  && !ce->local_port_defined && !ce->bind_defined)
2874  {
2875  ce->bind_local = false;
2876  }
2877 
2878  if (!ce->bind_local)
2879  {
2880  ce->local_port = NULL;
2881  }
2882 
2883  /* if protocol forcing is enabled, disable all protocols
2884  * except for the forced one
2885  */
2886  if (o->proto_force >= 0 && o->proto_force != ce->proto)
2887  {
2888  ce->flags |= CE_DISABLED;
2889  }
2890 
2891  /*
2892  * If --mssfix is supplied without a parameter, default
2893  * it to --fragment value, if --fragment is specified.
2894  */
2895  if (o->ce.mssfix_default)
2896  {
2897 #ifdef ENABLE_FRAGMENT
2898  if (ce->fragment)
2899  {
2900  ce->mssfix = ce->fragment;
2901  }
2902 #else
2903  msg(M_USAGE, "--mssfix must specify a parameter");
2904 #endif
2905  }
2906 
2907  /* our socks code is not fully IPv6 enabled yet (TCP works, UDP not)
2908  * so fall back to IPv4-only (trac #1221)
2909  */
2910  if (ce->socks_proxy_server && proto_is_udp(ce->proto) && ce->af != AF_INET)
2911  {
2912  if (ce->af == AF_INET6)
2913  {
2914  msg(M_INFO, "WARNING: '--proto udp6' is not compatible with "
2915  "'--socks-proxy' today. Forcing IPv4 mode." );
2916  }
2917  else
2918  {
2919  msg(M_INFO, "NOTICE: dual-stack mode for '--proto udp' does not "
2920  "work correctly with '--socks-proxy' today. Forcing IPv4." );
2921  }
2922  ce->af = AF_INET;
2923  }
2924 
2925  /*
2926  * Set MTU defaults
2927  */
2928  {
2929  if (!ce->tun_mtu_defined && !ce->link_mtu_defined)
2930  {
2931  ce->tun_mtu_defined = true;
2932  }
2933  if ((dev == DEV_TYPE_TAP) && !ce->tun_mtu_extra_defined)
2934  {
2935  ce->tun_mtu_extra_defined = true;
2936  ce->tun_mtu_extra = TAP_MTU_EXTRA_DEFAULT;
2937  }
2938  }
2939 
2940  /*
2941  * Set per-connection block tls-auth/crypt/crypto-v2 fields if undefined.
2942  *
2943  * At the end only one of these will be really set because the parser
2944  * logic prevents configurations where more are set.
2945  */
2946  if (!ce->tls_auth_file && !ce->tls_crypt_file && !ce->tls_crypt_v2_file)
2947  {
2948  ce->tls_auth_file = o->tls_auth_file;
2949  ce->tls_auth_file_inline = o->tls_auth_file_inline;
2950  ce->key_direction = o->key_direction;
2951 
2952  ce->tls_crypt_file = o->tls_crypt_file;
2953  ce->tls_crypt_file_inline = o->tls_crypt_file_inline;
2954 
2955  ce->tls_crypt_v2_file = o->tls_crypt_v2_file;
2956  ce->tls_crypt_v2_file_inline = o->tls_crypt_v2_file_inline;
2957  }
2958 
2959  /* Pre-cache tls-auth/crypt(-v2) key file if persist-key was specified and
2960  * keys were not already embedded in the config file.
2961  */
2962  if (o->persist_key)
2963  {
2964  connection_entry_preload_key(&ce->tls_auth_file,
2965  &ce->tls_auth_file_inline, &o->gc);
2966  connection_entry_preload_key(&ce->tls_crypt_file,
2967  &ce->tls_crypt_file_inline, &o->gc);
2968  connection_entry_preload_key(&ce->tls_crypt_v2_file,
2969  &ce->tls_crypt_v2_file_inline, &o->gc);
2970  }
2971 }

2973 #ifdef _WIN32
2974 /* If iservice is in use, we need def1 method for redirect-gateway */
2975 static void
2976 remap_redirect_gateway_flags(struct options *opt)
2977 {
2978  if (opt->routes
2979  && opt->route_method == ROUTE_METHOD_SERVICE
2980  && opt->routes->flags & RG_REROUTE_GW
2981  && !(opt->routes->flags & RG_DEF1))
2982  {
2983  msg(M_INFO, "Flag 'def1' added to --redirect-gateway (iservice is in use)");
2984  opt->routes->flags |= RG_DEF1;
2985  }
2986 }
2987 #endif

2989 static void
2990 options_postprocess_mutate_invariant(struct options *options)
2991 {
2992 #ifdef _WIN32
2993  const int dev = dev_type_enum(options->dev, options->dev_type);
2994 #endif
2995 
2996  /*
2997  * In forking TCP server mode, you don't need to ifconfig
2998  * the tap device (the assumption is that it will be bridged).
2999  */
3000  if (options->inetd == INETD_NOWAIT)
3001  {
3002  options->ifconfig_noexec = true;
3003  }
3004 
3005 #ifdef _WIN32
3006  /* when using wintun, kernel doesn't send DHCP requests, so don't use it */
3007  if (options->windows_driver == WINDOWS_DRIVER_WINTUN
3008  && (options->tuntap_options.ip_win32_type == IPW32_SET_DHCP_MASQ || options->tuntap_options.ip_win32_type == IPW32_SET_ADAPTIVE))
3009  {
3010  options->tuntap_options.ip_win32_type = IPW32_SET_NETSH;
3011  }
3012 
3013  if ((dev == DEV_TYPE_TUN || dev == DEV_TYPE_TAP) && !options->route_delay_defined)
3014  {
3015  /* delay may only be necessary when we perform DHCP handshake */
3016  const bool dhcp = (options->tuntap_options.ip_win32_type == IPW32_SET_DHCP_MASQ)
3017  || (options->tuntap_options.ip_win32_type == IPW32_SET_ADAPTIVE);
3018  if ((options->mode == MODE_POINT_TO_POINT) && dhcp)
3019  {
3020  options->route_delay_defined = true;
3021  options->route_delay = 5; /* Vista sometimes has a race without this */
3022  }
3023  }
3024 
3025  if (options->ifconfig_noexec)
3026  {
3027  options->tuntap_options.ip_win32_type = IPW32_SET_MANUAL;
3028  options->ifconfig_noexec = false;
3029  }
3030 
3031  remap_redirect_gateway_flags(options);
3032 
3033  /*
3034  * Check consistency of --mode server options.
3035  */
3036  if (options->mode == MODE_SERVER)
3037  {
3038  /*
3039  * We need to explicitly set --tap-sleep because
3040  * we do not schedule event timers in the top-level context.
3041  */
3042  options->tuntap_options.tap_sleep = 10;
3043  if (options->route_delay_defined && options->route_delay)
3044  {
3045  options->tuntap_options.tap_sleep = options->route_delay;
3046  }
3047  options->route_delay_defined = false;
3048  }
3049 #endif /* ifdef _WIN32 */
3050 
3051 #ifdef DEFAULT_PKCS11_MODULE
3052  /* If p11-kit is present on the system then load its p11-kit-proxy.so
3053  * by default if the user asks for PKCS#11 without otherwise specifying
3054  * the module to use. */
3055  if (!options->pkcs11_providers[0]
3056  && (options->pkcs11_id || options->pkcs11_id_management))
3057  {
3058  options->pkcs11_providers[0] = DEFAULT_PKCS11_MODULE;
3059  }
3060 #endif
3061 }

3063 static void
3064 options_postprocess_verify(const struct options *o)
3065 {
3066  if (o->connection_list)
3067  {
3068  int i;
3069  for (i = 0; i < o->connection_list->len; ++i)
3070  {
3071  options_postprocess_verify_ce(o, o->connection_list->array[i]);
3072  }
3073  }
3074  else
3075  {
3076  options_postprocess_verify_ce(o, &o->ce);
3077  }
3078 }
3079 
3080 static void
3081 options_postprocess_cipher(struct options *o)
3082 {
3083  if (!o->pull && !(o->mode == MODE_SERVER))
3084  {
3085  /* we are in the classic P2P mode */
3086  o->ncp_enabled = false;
3087  msg( M_WARN, "Cipher negotiation is disabled since neither "
3088  "P2MP client nor server mode is enabled");
3089 
3090  /* If the cipher is not set, use the old default of BF-CBC. We will
3091  * warn that this is deprecated on cipher initialisation, no need
3092  * to warn here as well */
3093  if (!o->ciphername)
3094  {
3095  o->ciphername = "BF-CBC";
3096  }
3097  return;
3098  }
3099 
3100  /* pull or P2MP mode */
3101  if (!o->ciphername)
3102  {
3103  if (!o->ncp_enabled)
3104  {
3105  msg(M_USAGE, "--ncp-disable needs an explicit --cipher or "
3106  "--data-ciphers-fallback config option");
3107  }
3108 
3109  msg(M_WARN, "--cipher is not set. Previous OpenVPN version defaulted to "
3110  "BF-CBC as fallback when cipher negotiation failed in this case. "
3111  "If you need this fallback please add '--data-ciphers-fallback "
3112  "BF-CBC' to your configuration and/or add BF-CBC to "
3113  "--data-ciphers.");
3114 
3115  /* We still need to set the ciphername to BF-CBC since various other
3116  * parts of OpenVPN assert that the ciphername is set */
3117  o->ciphername = "BF-CBC";
3118  }
3119  else if (!o->enable_ncp_fallback
3120  && !tls_item_in_cipher_list(o->ciphername, o->ncp_ciphers))
3121  {
3122  msg(M_WARN, "DEPRECATED OPTION: --cipher set to '%s' but missing in"
3123  " --data-ciphers (%s). Future OpenVPN version will "
3124  "ignore --cipher for cipher negotiations. "
3125  "Add '%s' to --data-ciphers or change --cipher '%s' to "
3126  "--data-ciphers-fallback '%s' to silence this warning.",
3127  o->ciphername, o->ncp_ciphers, o->ciphername,
3128  o->ciphername, o->ciphername);
3129  o->enable_ncp_fallback = true;
3130 
3131  /* Append the --cipher to ncp_ciphers to allow it in NCP */
3132  size_t newlen = strlen(o->ncp_ciphers) + 1 + strlen(o->ciphername) + 1;
3133  char *ncp_ciphers = gc_malloc(newlen, false, &o->gc);
3134 
3135  ASSERT(openvpn_snprintf(ncp_ciphers, newlen, "%s:%s", o->ncp_ciphers,
3136  o->ciphername));
3137  o->ncp_ciphers = ncp_ciphers;
3138  }
3139 }
3140 
3141 static void
3142 options_postprocess_mutate(struct options *o)
3143 {
3144  int i;
3145  /*
3146  * Process helper-type options which map to other, more complex
3147  * sequences of options.
3148  */
3149  helper_client_server(o);
3150  helper_keepalive(o);
3151  helper_tcp_nodelay(o);
3152 
3153  options_postprocess_cipher(o);
3154  options_postprocess_mutate_invariant(o);
3155 
3156  if (o->ncp_enabled)
3157  {
3158  o->ncp_ciphers = mutate_ncp_cipher_list(o->ncp_ciphers, &o->gc);
3159  if (o->ncp_ciphers == NULL)
3160  {
3161  msg(M_USAGE, "NCP cipher list contains unsupported ciphers or is too long.");
3162  }
3163  }
3164 
3165  if (o->remote_list && !o->connection_list)
3166  {
3167  /*
3168  * Convert remotes into connection list
3169  */
3170  const struct remote_list *rl = o->remote_list;
3171  for (i = 0; i < rl->len; ++i)
3172  {
3173  const struct remote_entry *re = rl->array[i];
3174  struct connection_entry ce = o->ce;
3175  struct connection_entry *ace;
3176 
3177  ASSERT(re->remote);
3178  connection_entry_load_re(&ce, re);
3179  ace = alloc_connection_entry(o, M_USAGE);
3180  ASSERT(ace);
3181  *ace = ce;
3182  }
3183  }
3184  else if (!o->remote_list && !o->connection_list)
3185  {
3186  struct connection_entry *ace;
3187  ace = alloc_connection_entry(o, M_USAGE);
3188  ASSERT(ace);
3189  *ace = o->ce;
3190  }
3191 
3192  ASSERT(o->connection_list);
3193  for (i = 0; i < o->connection_list->len; ++i)
3194  {
3195  options_postprocess_mutate_ce(o, o->connection_list->array[i]);
3196  }
3197 
3198  if (o->tls_server)
3199  {
3200  /* Check that DH file is specified, or explicitly disabled */
3201  notnull(o->dh_file, "DH file (--dh)");
3202  if (streq(o->dh_file, "none"))
3203  {
3204  o->dh_file = NULL;
3205  }
3206  }
3207  else if (o->dh_file)
3208  {
3209  /* DH file is only meaningful in a tls-server context. */
3210  msg(M_WARN, "WARNING: Ignoring option 'dh' in tls-client mode, please only "
3211  "include this in your server configuration");
3212  o->dh_file = NULL;
3213  }
3214 #if ENABLE_MANAGEMENT
3215  if (o->http_proxy_override)
3216  {
3217  options_postprocess_http_proxy_override(o);
3218  }
3219 #endif
3220 
3221 #if P2MP
3222  /*
3223  * Save certain parms before modifying options via --pull
3224  */
3225  pre_pull_save(o);
3226 #endif
3227 }
3228 
3229 /*
3230  * Check file/directory sanity
3231  *
3232  */
3233 #ifndef ENABLE_SMALL
3235 #define CHKACC_FILE (1<<0)
3236 #define CHKACC_DIRPATH (1<<1)
3237 #define CHKACC_FILEXSTWR (1<<2)
3238 #define CHKACC_ACPTSTDIN (1<<3)
3239 #define CHKACC_PRIVATE (1<<4)
3241 static bool
3242 check_file_access(const int type, const char *file, const int mode, const char *opt)
3243 {
3244  int errcode = 0;
3245 
3246  /* If no file configured, no errors to look for */
3247  if (!file)
3248  {
3249  return false;
3250  }
3251 
3252  /* If stdin is allowed and the file name is 'stdin', then do no
3253  * further checks as stdin is always available
3254  */
3255  if ( (type & CHKACC_ACPTSTDIN) && streq(file, "stdin") )
3256  {
3257  return false;
3258  }
3259 
3260  /* Is the directory path leading to the given file accessible? */
3261  if (type & CHKACC_DIRPATH)
3262  {
3263  char *fullpath = string_alloc(file, NULL); /* POSIX dirname() implementation may modify its arguments */
3264  char *dirpath = dirname(fullpath);
3265 
3266  if (platform_access(dirpath, mode|X_OK) != 0)
3267  {
3268  errcode = errno;
3269  }
3270  free(fullpath);
3271  }
3272 
3273  /* Is the file itself accessible? */
3274  if (!errcode && (type & CHKACC_FILE) && (platform_access(file, mode) != 0) )
3275  {
3276  errcode = errno;
3277  }
3278 
3279  /* If the file exists and is accessible, is it writable? */
3280  if (!errcode && (type & CHKACC_FILEXSTWR) && (platform_access(file, F_OK) == 0) )
3281  {
3282  if (platform_access(file, W_OK) != 0)
3283  {
3284  errcode = errno;
3285  }
3286  }
3287 
3288  /* Warn if a given private file is group/others accessible. */
3289  if (type & CHKACC_PRIVATE)
3290  {
3291  platform_stat_t st;
3292  if (platform_stat(file, &st))
3293  {
3294  msg(M_WARN | M_ERRNO, "WARNING: cannot stat file '%s'", file);
3295  }
3296 #ifndef _WIN32
3297  else
3298  {
3299  if (st.st_mode & (S_IRWXG|S_IRWXO))
3300  {
3301  msg(M_WARN, "WARNING: file '%s' is group or others accessible", file);
3302  }
3303  }
3304 #endif
3305  }
3306 
3307  /* Scream if an error is found */
3308  if (errcode > 0)
3309  {
3310  msg(M_NOPREFIX | M_OPTERR | M_ERRNO, "%s fails with '%s'", opt, file);
3311  }
3312 
3313  /* Return true if an error occurred */
3314  return (errcode != 0 ? true : false);
3315 }
3316 
3317 /* A wrapper for check_file_access() which also takes a chroot directory.
3318  * If chroot is NULL, behaviour is exactly the same as calling check_file_access() directly,
3319  * otherwise it will look for the file inside the given chroot directory instead.
3320  */
3321 static bool
3322 check_file_access_chroot(const char *chroot, const int type, const char *file, const int mode, const char *opt)
3323 {
3324  bool ret = false;
3325 
3326  /* If no file configured, no errors to look for */
3327  if (!file)
3328  {
3329  return false;
3330  }
3331 
3332  /* If chroot is set, look for the file/directory inside the chroot */
3333  if (chroot)
3334  {
3335  struct gc_arena gc = gc_new();
3336  struct buffer chroot_file;
3337 
3338  chroot_file = prepend_dir(chroot, file, &gc);
3339  ret = check_file_access(type, BSTR(&chroot_file), mode, opt);
3340  gc_free(&gc);
3341  }
3342  else
3343  {
3344  /* No chroot in play, just call core file check function */
3345  ret = check_file_access(type, file, mode, opt);
3346  }
3347  return ret;
3348 }
3349 
3354 static bool
3355 check_file_access_chroot_inline(bool is_inline, const char *chroot,
3356  const int type, const char *file,
3357  const int mode, const char *opt)
3358 {
3359  if (is_inline)
3360  {
3361  return false;
3362  }
3363 
3364  return check_file_access_chroot(chroot, type, file, mode, opt);
3365 }
3366 
3371 static bool
3372 check_file_access_inline(bool is_inline, const int type, const char *file,
3373  const int mode, const char *opt)
3374 {
3375  if (is_inline)
3376  {
3377  return false;
3378  }
3379 
3380  return check_file_access(type, file, mode, opt);
3381 }
3382 
3383 /*
3384  * Verifies that the path in the "command" that comes after certain script options (e.g., --up) is a
3385  * valid file with appropriate permissions.
3386  *
3387  * "command" consists of a path, optionally followed by a space, which may be
3388  * followed by arbitrary arguments. It is NOT a full shell command line -- shell expansion is not
3389  * performed.
3390  *
3391  * The path and arguments in "command" may be single- or double-quoted or escaped.
3392  *
3393  * The path is extracted from "command", then check_file_access() is called to check it. The
3394  * arguments, if any, are ignored.
3395  *
3396  * Note that the type, mode, and opt arguments to this routine are the same as the corresponding
3397  * check_file_access() arguments.
3398  */
3399 static bool
3400 check_cmd_access(const char *command, const char *opt, const char *chroot)
3401 {
3402  struct argv argv;
3403  bool return_code;
3404 
3405  /* If no command was set, there are no errors to look for */
3406  if (!command)
3407  {
3408  return false;
3409  }
3410 
3411  /* Extract executable path and arguments */
3412  argv = argv_new();
3413  argv_parse_cmd(&argv, command);
3414 
3415  /* if an executable is specified then check it; otherwise, complain */
3416  if (argv.argv[0])
3417  {
3418  /* Scripts requires R_OK as well, but that might fail on binaries which
3419  * only requires X_OK to function on Unix - a scenario not unlikely to
3420  * be seen on suid binaries.
3421  */
3422  return_code = check_file_access_chroot(chroot, CHKACC_FILE, argv.argv[0], X_OK, opt);
3423  }
3424  else
3425  {
3426  msg(M_NOPREFIX|M_OPTERR, "%s fails with '%s': No path to executable.",
3427  opt, command);
3428  return_code = true;
3429  }
3430 
3431  argv_free(&argv);
3432 
3433  return return_code;
3434 }
3435 
3436 /*
3437  * Sanity check of all file/dir options. Checks that file/dir
3438  * is accessible by OpenVPN
3439  */
3440 static void
3441 options_postprocess_filechecks(struct options *options)
3442 {
3443  bool errs = false;
3444 
3445  /* ** SSL/TLS/crypto related files ** */
3446  errs |= check_file_access_inline(options->dh_file_inline, CHKACC_FILE,
3447  options->dh_file, R_OK, "--dh");
3448 
3449  errs |= check_file_access_inline(options->ca_file_inline, CHKACC_FILE,
3450  options->ca_file, R_OK, "--ca");
3451 
3452  errs |= check_file_access_chroot(options->chroot_dir, CHKACC_FILE,
3453  options->ca_path, R_OK, "--capath");
3454 
3455  errs |= check_file_access_inline(options->cert_file_inline, CHKACC_FILE,
3456  options->cert_file, R_OK, "--cert");
3457 
3458  errs |= check_file_access_inline(options->extra_certs_file, CHKACC_FILE,
3459  options->extra_certs_file, R_OK,
3460  "--extra-certs");
3461 
3462 #ifdef ENABLE_MANAGMENT
3463  if (!(options->management_flags & MF_EXTERNAL_KEY))
3464 #endif
3465  {
3466  errs |= check_file_access_inline(options->priv_key_file_inline,
3467  CHKACC_FILE|CHKACC_PRIVATE,
3468  options->priv_key_file, R_OK, "--key");
3469  }
3470 
3471  errs |= check_file_access_inline(options->pkcs12_file_inline,
3472  CHKACC_FILE|CHKACC_PRIVATE,
3473  options->pkcs12_file, R_OK, "--pkcs12");
3474 
3475  if (options->ssl_flags & SSLF_CRL_VERIFY_DIR)
3476  {
3477  errs |= check_file_access_chroot(options->chroot_dir, CHKACC_FILE,
3478  options->crl_file, R_OK|X_OK,
3479  "--crl-verify directory");
3480  }
3481  else
3482  {
3483  errs |= check_file_access_chroot_inline(options->crl_file_inline,
3484  options->chroot_dir,
3485  CHKACC_FILE, options->crl_file,
3486  R_OK, "--crl-verify");
3487  }
3488 
3489  ASSERT(options->connection_list);
3490  for (int i = 0; i < options->connection_list->len; ++i)
3491  {
3492  struct connection_entry *ce = options->connection_list->array[i];
3493 
3494  errs |= check_file_access_inline(ce->tls_auth_file_inline,
3495  CHKACC_FILE|CHKACC_PRIVATE,
3496  ce->tls_auth_file, R_OK,
3497  "--tls-auth");
3498  errs |= check_file_access_inline(ce->tls_crypt_file_inline,
3499  CHKACC_FILE|CHKACC_PRIVATE,
3500  ce->tls_crypt_file, R_OK,
3501  "--tls-crypt");
3502  errs |= check_file_access_inline(ce->tls_crypt_v2_file_inline,
3503  CHKACC_FILE|CHKACC_PRIVATE,
3504  ce->tls_crypt_v2_file, R_OK,
3505  "--tls-crypt-v2");
3506  }
3507 
3508  errs |= check_file_access_inline(options->shared_secret_file_inline,
3509  CHKACC_FILE|CHKACC_PRIVATE,
3510  options->shared_secret_file, R_OK,
3511  "--secret");
3512 
3513  errs |= check_file_access(CHKACC_DIRPATH|CHKACC_FILEXSTWR,
3514  options->packet_id_file, R_OK|W_OK, "--replay-persist");
3515 
3516  /* ** Password files ** */
3517  errs |= check_file_access(CHKACC_FILE|CHKACC_ACPTSTDIN|CHKACC_PRIVATE,
3518  options->key_pass_file, R_OK, "--askpass");
3519 #ifdef ENABLE_MANAGEMENT
3520  errs |= check_file_access(CHKACC_FILE|CHKACC_ACPTSTDIN|CHKACC_PRIVATE,
3521  options->management_user_pass, R_OK,
3522  "--management user/password file");
3523 #endif /* ENABLE_MANAGEMENT */
3524 #if P2MP
3525  errs |= check_file_access(CHKACC_FILE|CHKACC_ACPTSTDIN|CHKACC_PRIVATE,
3526  options->auth_user_pass_file, R_OK,
3527  "--auth-user-pass");
3528 #endif /* P2MP */
3529 
3530  /* ** System related ** */
3531  errs |= check_file_access(CHKACC_FILE, options->chroot_dir,
3532  R_OK|X_OK, "--chroot directory");
3533  errs |= check_file_access(CHKACC_DIRPATH|CHKACC_FILEXSTWR, options->writepid,
3534  R_OK|W_OK, "--writepid");
3535 
3536  /* ** Log related ** */
3537  errs |= check_file_access(CHKACC_DIRPATH|CHKACC_FILEXSTWR, options->status_file,
3538  R_OK|W_OK, "--status");
3539 
3540  /* ** Config related ** */
3541  errs |= check_file_access_chroot(options->chroot_dir, CHKACC_FILE, options->tls_export_cert,
3542  R_OK|W_OK|X_OK, "--tls-export-cert");
3543  errs |= check_file_access_chroot(options->chroot_dir, CHKACC_FILE, options->client_config_dir,
3544  R_OK|X_OK, "--client-config-dir");
3545  errs |= check_file_access_chroot(options->chroot_dir, CHKACC_FILE, options->tmp_dir,
3546  R_OK|W_OK|X_OK, "Temporary directory (--tmp-dir)");
3547 
3548  if (errs)
3549  {
3550  msg(M_USAGE, "Please correct these errors.");
3551  }
3552 }
3553 #endif /* !ENABLE_SMALL */
3554 
3555 /*
3556  * Sanity check on options.
3557  * Also set some options based on other
3558  * options.
3559  */
3560 void
3561 options_postprocess(struct options *options)
3562 {
3563  options_postprocess_mutate(options);
3564  options_postprocess_verify(options);
3565 #ifndef ENABLE_SMALL
3566  options_postprocess_filechecks(options);
3567 #endif /* !ENABLE_SMALL */
3568 }

3572 /*
3573  * Save/Restore certain option defaults before --pull is applied.
3574  */
3575 
3576 void
3577 pre_pull_save(struct options *o)
3578 {
3579  if (o->pull)
3580  {
3581  ALLOC_OBJ_CLEAR_GC(o->pre_pull, struct options_pre_pull, &o->gc);
3582  o->pre_pull->tuntap_options = o->tuntap_options;
3583  o->pre_pull->tuntap_options_defined = true;
3584  o->pre_pull->foreign_option_index = o->foreign_option_index;
3585  if (o->routes)
3586  {
3587  o->pre_pull->routes = clone_route_option_list(o->routes, &o->gc);
3588  o->pre_pull->routes_defined = true;
3589  }
3590  if (o->routes_ipv6)
3591  {
3592  o->pre_pull->routes_ipv6 = clone_route_ipv6_option_list(o->routes_ipv6, &o->gc);
3593  o->pre_pull->routes_ipv6_defined = true;
3594  }
3595  if (o->client_nat)
3596  {
3597  o->pre_pull->client_nat = clone_client_nat_option_list(o->client_nat, &o->gc);
3598  o->pre_pull->client_nat_defined = true;
3599  }
3600 
3601  o->pre_pull->route_default_gateway = o->route_default_gateway;
3602  o->pre_pull->route_ipv6_default_gateway = o->route_ipv6_default_gateway;
3603 
3604  /* Ping related options should be reset to the config values on reconnect */
3605  o->pre_pull->ping_rec_timeout = o->ping_rec_timeout;
3606  o->pre_pull->ping_rec_timeout_action = o->ping_rec_timeout_action;
3607  o->pre_pull->ping_send_timeout = o->ping_send_timeout;
3608  }
3609 }
3610 
3611 void
3612 pre_pull_restore(struct options *o, struct gc_arena *gc)
3613 {
3614  const struct options_pre_pull *pp = o->pre_pull;
3615  if (pp)
3616  {
3617  CLEAR(o->tuntap_options);
3618  if (pp->tuntap_options_defined)
3619  {
3620  o->tuntap_options = pp->tuntap_options;
3621  }
3622 
3623  if (pp->routes_defined)
3624  {
3625  rol_check_alloc(o);
3626  copy_route_option_list(o->routes, pp->routes, gc);
3627  }
3628  else
3629  {
3630  o->routes = NULL;
3631  }
3632 
3633  if (pp->routes_ipv6_defined)
3634  {
3635  rol6_check_alloc(o);
3636  copy_route_ipv6_option_list(o->routes_ipv6, pp->routes_ipv6, gc);
3637  }
3638  else
3639  {
3640  o->routes_ipv6 = NULL;
3641  }
3642 
3643  o->route_default_gateway = pp->route_default_gateway;
3644  o->route_ipv6_default_gateway = pp->route_ipv6_default_gateway;
3645 
3646  if (pp->client_nat_defined)
3647  {
3648  cnol_check_alloc(o);
3649  copy_client_nat_option_list(o->client_nat, pp->client_nat);
3650  }
3651  else
3652  {
3653  o->client_nat = NULL;
3654  }
3655 
3656  o->foreign_option_index = pp->foreign_option_index;
3657 
3658  o->ping_rec_timeout = pp->ping_rec_timeout;
3659  o->ping_rec_timeout_action = pp->ping_rec_timeout_action;
3660  o->ping_send_timeout = pp->ping_send_timeout;
3661  }
3662 
3663  o->push_continuation = 0;
3664  o->push_option_types_found = 0;
3665 }

3668 
3675 static size_t
3676 calc_options_string_link_mtu(const struct options *o, const struct frame *frame)
3677 {
3678  size_t link_mtu = EXPANDED_SIZE(frame);
3679 
3680  if (o->pull || o->mode == MODE_SERVER)
3681  {
3682  struct frame fake_frame = *frame;
3683  struct key_type fake_kt;
3684 
3685  frame_remove_from_extra_frame(&fake_frame, crypto_max_overhead());
3686 
3687 
3688  /* o->ciphername might be BF-CBC even though the underlying SSL library
3689  * does not support it. For this reason we workaround this corner case
3690  * by pretending to have no encryption enabled and by manually adding
3691  * the required packet overhead to the MTU computation.
3692  */
3693  const char *ciphername = o->ciphername;
3694 
3695  if (strcmp(o->ciphername, "BF-CBC") == 0)
3696  {
3697  /* none has no overhead, so use this to later add only --auth
3698  * overhead */
3699 
3700  /* overhead of BF-CBC: 64 bit block size, 64 bit IV size */
3701  frame_add_to_extra_frame(&fake_frame, 64/8 + 64/8);
3702  ciphername = "none";
3703  }
3704 
3705  init_key_type(&fake_kt, ciphername, o->authname, o->keysize, true,
3706  false);
3707 
3708  crypto_adjust_frame_parameters(&fake_frame, &fake_kt, o->replay,
3709  cipher_kt_mode_ofb_cfb(fake_kt.cipher));
3710  frame_finalize(&fake_frame, o->ce.link_mtu_defined, o->ce.link_mtu,
3711  o->ce.tun_mtu_defined, o->ce.tun_mtu);
3712  msg(D_MTU_DEBUG, "%s: link-mtu %u -> %d", __func__, (unsigned int) link_mtu,
3713  EXPANDED_SIZE(&fake_frame));
3714  link_mtu = EXPANDED_SIZE(&fake_frame);
3715  }
3716  return link_mtu;
3717 }
3718 /*
3719  * Build an options string to represent data channel encryption options.
3720  * This string must match exactly between peers. The keysize is checked
3721  * separately by read_key().
3722  *
3723  * The following options must match on both peers:
3724  *
3725  * Tunnel options:
3726  *
3727  * --dev tun|tap [unit number need not match]
3728  * --dev-type tun|tap
3729  * --link-mtu
3730  * --udp-mtu
3731  * --tun-mtu
3732  * --proto udp
3733  * --proto tcp-client [matched with --proto tcp-server
3734  * on the other end of the connection]
3735  * --proto tcp-server [matched with --proto tcp-client on
3736  * the other end of the connection]
3737  * --tun-ipv6
3738  * --ifconfig x y [matched with --ifconfig y x on
3739  * the other end of the connection]
3740  *
3741  * --comp-lzo
3742  * --compress alg
3743  * --fragment
3744  *
3745  * Crypto Options:
3746  *
3747  * --cipher
3748  * --auth
3749  * --keysize
3750  * --secret
3751  * --no-replay
3752  *
3753  * SSL Options:
3754  *
3755  * --tls-auth
3756  * --tls-client [matched with --tls-server on
3757  * the other end of the connection]
3758  * --tls-server [matched with --tls-client on
3759  * the other end of the connection]
3760  */
3761 char *
3762 options_string(const struct options *o,
3763  const struct frame *frame,
3764  struct tuntap *tt,
3765  openvpn_net_ctx_t *ctx,
3766  bool remote,
3767  struct gc_arena *gc)
3768 {
3769  struct buffer out = alloc_buf(OPTION_LINE_SIZE);
3770  bool tt_local = false;
3771 
3772  buf_printf(&out, "V4");
3773 
3774  /*
3775  * Tunnel Options
3776  */
3777 
3778  buf_printf(&out, ",dev-type %s", dev_type_string(o->dev, o->dev_type));
3779  /* the link-mtu that we send has only a meaning if have a fixed
3780  * cipher (p2p) or have a fallback cipher configured for older non
3781  * ncp clients. But not sending it will make even 2.4 complain
3782  * about it being missing. So still send it. */
3783  buf_printf(&out, ",link-mtu %u",
3784  (unsigned int) calc_options_string_link_mtu(o, frame));
3785 
3786  buf_printf(&out, ",tun-mtu %d", PAYLOAD_SIZE(frame));
3787  buf_printf(&out, ",proto %s", proto_remote(o->ce.proto, remote));
3788 
3789  bool p2p_nopull = o->mode == MODE_POINT_TO_POINT && !PULL_DEFINED(o);
3790  /* send tun_ipv6 only in peer2peer mode - in client/server mode, it
3791  * is usually pushed by the server, triggering a non-helpful warning
3792  */
3793  if (o->ifconfig_ipv6_local && p2p_nopull)
3794  {
3795  buf_printf(&out, ",tun-ipv6");
3796  }
3797 
3798  /*
3799  * Try to get ifconfig parameters into the options string.
3800  * If tt is undefined, make a temporary instantiation.
3801  */
3802  if (!tt)
3803  {
3804  tt = init_tun(o->dev,
3805  o->dev_type,
3806  o->topology,
3807  o->ifconfig_local,
3808  o->ifconfig_remote_netmask,
3809  o->ifconfig_ipv6_local,
3810  o->ifconfig_ipv6_netbits,
3811  o->ifconfig_ipv6_remote,
3812  NULL,
3813  NULL,
3814  false,
3815  NULL,
3816  ctx);
3817  if (tt)
3818  {
3819  tt_local = true;
3820  }
3821  }
3822 
3823  if (tt && p2p_nopull)
3824  {
3825  const char *ios = ifconfig_options_string(tt, remote, o->ifconfig_nowarn, gc);
3826  if (ios && strlen(ios))
3827  {
3828  buf_printf(&out, ",ifconfig %s", ios);
3829  }
3830  }
3831  if (tt_local)
3832  {
3833  free(tt);
3834  tt = NULL;
3835  }
3836 
3837 #ifdef USE_COMP
3838  if (o->comp.alg != COMP_ALG_UNDEF)
3839  {
3840  buf_printf(&out, ",comp-lzo"); /* for compatibility, this simply indicates that compression context is active, not necessarily LZO per-se */
3841  }
3842 #endif
3843 
3844 #ifdef ENABLE_FRAGMENT
3845  if (o->ce.fragment)
3846  {
3847  buf_printf(&out, ",mtu-dynamic");
3848  }
3849 #endif
3850 
3851 #define TLS_CLIENT (o->tls_client)
3852 #define TLS_SERVER (o->tls_server)
3853 
3854  /*
3855  * Key direction
3856  */
3857  {
3858  const char *kd = keydirection2ascii(o->key_direction, remote, false);
3859  if (kd)
3860  {
3861  buf_printf(&out, ",keydir %s", kd);
3862  }
3863  }
3864 
3865  /*
3866  * Crypto Options
3867  */
3868  if (o->shared_secret_file || TLS_CLIENT || TLS_SERVER)
3869  {
3870  struct key_type kt;
3871 
3872  ASSERT((o->shared_secret_file != NULL)
3873  + (TLS_CLIENT == true)
3874  + (TLS_SERVER == true)
3875  <= 1);
3876 
3877  /* Skip resolving BF-CBC to allow SSL libraries without BF-CBC
3878  * to work here in the default configuration */
3879  const char *ciphername = o->ciphername;
3880  int keysize;
3881 
3882  if (strcmp(o->ciphername, "BF-CBC") == 0)
3883  {
3884  init_key_type(&kt, "none", o->authname, o->keysize, true,
3885  false);
3886  keysize = 128;
3887  }
3888  else
3889  {
3890  init_key_type(&kt, o->ciphername, o->authname, o->keysize, true,
3891  false);
3892  ciphername = cipher_kt_name(kt.cipher);
3893  keysize = kt.cipher_length * 8;
3894  }
3895  /* Only announce the cipher to our peer if we are willing to
3896  * support it */
3897  if (p2p_nopull || !o->ncp_enabled
3898  || tls_item_in_cipher_list(ciphername, o->ncp_ciphers))
3899  {
3900  buf_printf(&out, ",cipher %s", ciphername);
3901  }
3902  buf_printf(&out, ",auth %s", md_kt_name(kt.digest));
3903  buf_printf(&out, ",keysize %d", keysize);
3904  if (o->shared_secret_file)
3905  {
3906  buf_printf(&out, ",secret");
3907  }
3908  if (!o->replay)
3909  {
3910  buf_printf(&out, ",no-replay");
3911  }
3912 
3913 #ifdef ENABLE_PREDICTION_RESISTANCE
3914  if (o->use_prediction_resistance)
3915  {
3916  buf_printf(&out, ",use-prediction-resistance");
3917  }
3918 #endif
3919  }
3920 
3921  /*
3922  * SSL Options
3923  */
3924  {
3925  if (TLS_CLIENT || TLS_SERVER)
3926  {
3927  if (o->ce.tls_auth_file)
3928  {
3929  buf_printf(&out, ",tls-auth");
3930  }
3931  /* Not adding tls-crypt here, because we won't reach this code if
3932  * tls-auth/tls-crypt does not match. Removing tls-auth here would
3933  * break stuff, so leaving that in place. */
3934 
3935  buf_printf(&out, ",key-method %d", KEY_METHOD_2);
3936  }
3937 
3938  if (remote)
3939  {
3940  if (TLS_CLIENT)
3941  {
3942  buf_printf(&out, ",tls-server");
3943  }
3944  else if (TLS_SERVER)
3945  {
3946  buf_printf(&out, ",tls-client");
3947  }
3948  }
3949  else
3950  {
3951  if (TLS_CLIENT)
3952  {
3953  buf_printf(&out, ",tls-client");
3954  }
3955  else if (TLS_SERVER)
3956  {
3957  buf_printf(&out, ",tls-server");
3958  }
3959  }
3960  }
3961 
3962 #undef TLS_CLIENT
3963 #undef TLS_SERVER
3964 
3965  return BSTR(&out);
3966 }
3967 
3968 /*
3969  * Compare option strings for equality.
3970  * If the first two chars of the strings differ, it means that
3971  * we are looking at different versions of the options string,
3972  * therefore don't compare them and return true.
3973  */
3974 
3975 bool
3976 options_cmp_equal(char *actual, const char *expected)
3977 {
3978  return options_cmp_equal_safe(actual, expected, strlen(actual) + 1);
3979 }
3980 
3981 void
3982 options_warning(char *actual, const char *expected)
3983 {
3984  options_warning_safe(actual, expected, strlen(actual) + 1);
3985 }
3986 
3987 static const char *
3988 options_warning_extract_parm1(const char *option_string,
3989  struct gc_arena *gc_ret)
3990 {
3991  struct gc_arena gc = gc_new();
3992  struct buffer b = string_alloc_buf(option_string, &gc);
3993  char *p = gc_malloc(OPTION_PARM_SIZE, false, &gc);
3994  const char *ret;
3995 
3996  buf_parse(&b, ' ', p, OPTION_PARM_SIZE);
3997  ret = string_alloc(p, gc_ret);
3998  gc_free(&gc);
3999  return ret;
4000 }
4001 
4002 static void
4003 options_warning_safe_scan2(const int msglevel,
4004  const int delim,
4005  const bool report_inconsistent,
4006  const char *p1,
4007  const struct buffer *b2_src,
4008  const char *b1_name,
4009  const char *b2_name)
4010 {
4011  /* We will stop sending 'key-method', 'keydir', 'proto' and 'tls-auth' in
4012  * OCC in a future version (because it's not useful). To reduce questions
4013  * when interoperating, we no longer printing a warning about it.
4014  */
4015  if (strprefix(p1, "key-method ")
4016  || strprefix(p1, "keydir ")
4017  || strprefix(p1, "proto ")
4018  || streq(p1, "tls-auth")
4019  || strprefix(p1, "tun-ipv6")
4020  || strprefix(p1, "cipher "))
4021  {
4022  return;
4023  }
4024 
4025  if (strlen(p1) > 0)
4026  {
4027  struct gc_arena gc = gc_new();
4028  struct buffer b2 = *b2_src;
4029  const char *p1_prefix = options_warning_extract_parm1(p1, &gc);
4030  char *p2 = gc_malloc(OPTION_PARM_SIZE, false, &gc);
4031 
4032  while (buf_parse(&b2, delim, p2, OPTION_PARM_SIZE))
4033  {
4034  if (strlen(p2))
4035  {
4036  const char *p2_prefix = options_warning_extract_parm1(p2, &gc);
4037 
4038  if (!strcmp(p1, p2))
4039  {
4040  goto done;
4041  }
4042  if (!strcmp(p1_prefix, p2_prefix))
4043  {
4044  if (report_inconsistent)
4045  {
4046  msg(msglevel, "WARNING: '%s' is used inconsistently, %s='%s', %s='%s'",
4047  safe_print(p1_prefix, &gc),
4048  b1_name,
4049  safe_print(p1, &gc),
4050  b2_name,
4051  safe_print(p2, &gc));
4052  }
4053  goto done;
4054  }
4055  }
4056  }
4057 
4058  msg(msglevel, "WARNING: '%s' is present in %s config but missing in %s config, %s='%s'",
4059  safe_print(p1_prefix, &gc),
4060  b1_name,
4061  b2_name,
4062  b1_name,
4063  safe_print(p1, &gc));
4064 
4065 done:
4066  gc_free(&gc);
4067  }
4068 }
4069 
4070 static void
4071 options_warning_safe_scan1(const int msglevel,
4072  const int delim,
4073  const bool report_inconsistent,
4074  const struct buffer *b1_src,
4075  const struct buffer *b2_src,
4076  const char *b1_name,
4077  const char *b2_name)
4078 {
4079  struct gc_arena gc = gc_new();
4080  struct buffer b = *b1_src;
4081  char *p = gc_malloc(OPTION_PARM_SIZE, true, &gc);
4082 
4083  while (buf_parse(&b, delim, p, OPTION_PARM_SIZE))
4084  {
4085  options_warning_safe_scan2(msglevel, delim, report_inconsistent, p, b2_src, b1_name, b2_name);
4086  }
4087 
4088  gc_free(&gc);
4089 }
4090 
4091 static void
4092 options_warning_safe_ml(const int msglevel, char *actual, const char *expected, size_t actual_n)
4093 {
4094  struct gc_arena gc = gc_new();
4095 
4096  if (actual_n > 0)
4097  {
4098  struct buffer local = alloc_buf_gc(OPTION_PARM_SIZE + 16, &gc);
4099  struct buffer remote = alloc_buf_gc(OPTION_PARM_SIZE + 16, &gc);
4100  actual[actual_n - 1] = 0;
4101 
4102  buf_printf(&local, "version %s", expected);
4103  buf_printf(&remote, "version %s", actual);
4104 
4105  options_warning_safe_scan1(msglevel, ',', true,
4106  &local, &remote,
4107  "local", "remote");
4108 
4109  options_warning_safe_scan1(msglevel, ',', false,
4110  &remote, &local,
4111  "remote", "local");
4112  }
4113 
4114  gc_free(&gc);
4115 }
4116 
4117 bool
4118 options_cmp_equal_safe(char *actual, const char *expected, size_t actual_n)
4119 {
4120  struct gc_arena gc = gc_new();
4121  bool ret = true;
4122 
4123  if (actual_n > 0)
4124  {
4125  actual[actual_n - 1] = 0;
4126 #ifndef ENABLE_STRICT_OPTIONS_CHECK
4127  if (strncmp(actual, expected, 2))
4128  {
4129  msg(D_SHOW_OCC, "NOTE: Options consistency check may be skewed by version differences");
4130  options_warning_safe_ml(D_SHOW_OCC, actual, expected, actual_n);
4131  }
4132  else
4133 #endif
4134  ret = !strcmp(actual, expected);
4135  }
4136  gc_free(&gc);
4137  return ret;
4138 }

4140 void
4141 options_warning_safe(char *actual, const char *expected, size_t actual_n)

4144 }

4154 char *
4155 options_string_extract_option(const char *options_string,const char *opt_name,
4156  struct gc_arena *gc)
4157 {
4158  char *ret = NULL;
4159  const size_t opt_name_len = strlen(opt_name);
4160 
4161  const char *p = options_string;
4162  while (p)
4163  {
4164  if (0 == strncmp(p, opt_name, opt_name_len)
4165  && strlen(p) > (opt_name_len+1) && p[opt_name_len] == ' ')
4166  {
4167  /* option found, extract value */
4168  const char *start = &p[opt_name_len+1];
4169  const char *end = strchr(p, ',');
4170  size_t val_len = end ? end - start : strlen(start);
4171  ret = gc_malloc(val_len+1, true, gc);
4172  memcpy(ret, start, val_len);
4173  break;
4174  }
4175  p = strchr(p, ',');
4176  if (p)
4177  {
4178  p++; /* skip delimiter */
4179  }
4180  }
4181  return ret;
4182 }

4184 static void
4185 foreign_option(struct options *o, char *argv[], int len, struct env_set *es)
4186 {
4187  if (len > 0)
4188  {
4189  struct gc_arena gc = gc_new();
4190  struct buffer name = alloc_buf_gc(OPTION_PARM_SIZE, &gc);
4191  struct buffer value = alloc_buf_gc(OPTION_PARM_SIZE, &gc);
4192  int i;
4193  bool first = true;
4194  bool good = true;
4195 
4196  good &= buf_printf(&name, "foreign_option_%d", o->foreign_option_index + 1);
4197  ++o->foreign_option_index;
4198  for (i = 0; i < len; ++i)
4199  {
4200  if (argv[i])
4201  {
4202  if (!first)
4203  {
4204  good &= buf_printf(&value, " ");
4205  }
4206  good &= buf_printf(&value, "%s", argv[i]);
4207  first = false;
4208  }
4209  }
4210  if (good)
4211  {
4212  setenv_str(es, BSTR(&name), BSTR(&value));
4213  }
4214  else
4215  {
4216  msg(M_WARN, "foreign_option: name/value overflow");
4217  }
4218  gc_free(&gc);
4219  }
4220 }

4490 static inline bool
4491 space(unsigned char c)
4492 {
4493  return c == '\0' || isspace(c);
4494 }
4495 
4496 int
4497 parse_line(const char *line,
4498  char *p[],
4499  const int n,
4500  const char *file,
4501  const int line_num,
4502  int msglevel,
4503  struct gc_arena *gc)
4504 {
4505  const int STATE_INITIAL = 0;
4506  const int STATE_READING_QUOTED_PARM = 1;
4507  const int STATE_READING_UNQUOTED_PARM = 2;
4508  const int STATE_DONE = 3;
4509  const int STATE_READING_SQUOTED_PARM = 4;
4510 
4511  const char *error_prefix = "";
4512 
4513  int ret = 0;
4514  const char *c = line;
4515  int state = STATE_INITIAL;
4516  bool backslash = false;
4517  char in, out;
4518 
4519  char parm[OPTION_PARM_SIZE];
4520  unsigned int parm_len = 0;
4521 
4522  msglevel &= ~M_OPTERR;
4523 
4524  if (msglevel & M_MSG_VIRT_OUT)
4525  {
4526  error_prefix = "ERROR: ";
4527  }
4528 
4529  do
4530  {
4531  in = *c;
4532  out = 0;
4533 
4534  if (!backslash && in == '\\' && state != STATE_READING_SQUOTED_PARM)
4535  {
4536  backslash = true;
4537  }
4538  else
4539  {
4540  if (state == STATE_INITIAL)
4541  {
4542  if (!space(in))
4543  {
4544  if (in == ';' || in == '#') /* comment */
4545  {
4546  break;
4547  }
4548  if (!backslash && in == '\"')
4549  {
4550  state = STATE_READING_QUOTED_PARM;
4551  }
4552  else if (!backslash && in == '\'')
4553  {
4554  state = STATE_READING_SQUOTED_PARM;
4555  }
4556  else
4557  {
4558  out = in;
4559  state = STATE_READING_UNQUOTED_PARM;
4560  }
4561  }
4562  }
4563  else if (state == STATE_READING_UNQUOTED_PARM)
4564  {
4565  if (!backslash && space(in))
4566  {
4567  state = STATE_DONE;
4568  }
4569  else
4570  {
4571  out = in;
4572  }
4573  }
4574  else if (state == STATE_READING_QUOTED_PARM)
4575  {
4576  if (!backslash && in == '\"')
4577  {
4578  state = STATE_DONE;
4579  }
4580  else
4581  {
4582  out = in;
4583  }
4584  }
4585  else if (state == STATE_READING_SQUOTED_PARM)
4586  {
4587  if (in == '\'')
4588  {
4589  state = STATE_DONE;
4590  }
4591  else
4592  {
4593  out = in;
4594  }
4595  }
4596  if (state == STATE_DONE)
4597  {
4598  /* ASSERT (parm_len > 0); */
4599  p[ret] = gc_malloc(parm_len + 1, true, gc);
4600  memcpy(p[ret], parm, parm_len);
4601  p[ret][parm_len] = '\0';
4602  state = STATE_INITIAL;
4603  parm_len = 0;
4604  ++ret;
4605  }
4606 
4607  if (backslash && out)
4608  {
4609  if (!(out == '\\' || out == '\"' || space(out)))
4610  {
4611 #ifdef ENABLE_SMALL
4612  msg(msglevel, "%sOptions warning: Bad backslash ('\\') usage in %s:%d", error_prefix, file, line_num);
4613 #else
4614  msg(msglevel, "%sOptions warning: Bad backslash ('\\') usage in %s:%d: remember that backslashes are treated as shell-escapes and if you need to pass backslash characters as part of a Windows filename, you should use double backslashes such as \"c:\\\\" PACKAGE "\\\\static.key\"", error_prefix, file, line_num);
4615 #endif
4616  return 0;
4617  }
4618  }
4619  backslash = false;
4620  }
4621 
4622  /* store parameter character */
4623  if (out)
4624  {
4625  if (parm_len >= SIZE(parm))
4626  {
4627  parm[SIZE(parm) - 1] = 0;
4628  msg(msglevel, "%sOptions error: Parameter at %s:%d is too long (%d chars max): %s",
4629  error_prefix, file, line_num, (int) SIZE(parm), parm);
4630  return 0;
4631  }
4632  parm[parm_len++] = out;
4633  }
4634 
4635  /* avoid overflow if too many parms in one config file line */
4636  if (ret >= n)
4637  {
4638  break;
4639  }
4640 
4641  } while (*c++ != '\0');
4642 
4643  if (state == STATE_READING_QUOTED_PARM)
4644  {
4645  msg(msglevel, "%sOptions error: No closing quotation (\") in %s:%d", error_prefix, file, line_num);
4646  return 0;
4647  }
4648  if (state == STATE_READING_SQUOTED_PARM)
4649  {
4650  msg(msglevel, "%sOptions error: No closing single quotation (\') in %s:%d", error_prefix, file, line_num);
4651  return 0;
4652  }
4653  if (state != STATE_INITIAL)
4654  {
4655  msg(msglevel, "%sOptions error: Residual parse state (%d) in %s:%d", error_prefix, state, file, line_num);
4656  return 0;
4657  }
4658 #if 0
4659  {
4660  int i;
4661  for (i = 0; i < ret; ++i)
4662  {
4663  msg(M_INFO|M_NOPREFIX, "%s:%d ARG[%d] '%s'", file, line_num, i, p[i]);
4664  }
4665  }
4666 #endif
4667  return ret;
4668 }

4670 static void
4671 bypass_doubledash(char **p)
4672 {
4673  if (strlen(*p) >= 3 && !strncmp(*p, "--", 2))
4674  {
4675  *p += 2;
4676  }
4677 }
4678 
4679 struct in_src {
4680 #define IS_TYPE_FP 1
4681 #define IS_TYPE_BUF 2
4682  int type;
4683  union {
4684  FILE *fp;
4685  struct buffer *multiline;
4686  } u;
4687 };
4688 
4689 static bool
4690 in_src_get(const struct in_src *is, char *line, const int size)
4691 {
4692  if (is->type == IS_TYPE_FP)
4693  {
4694  return BOOL_CAST(fgets(line, size, is->u.fp));
4695  }
4696  else if (is->type == IS_TYPE_BUF)
4697  {
4698  bool status = buf_parse(is->u.multiline, '\n', line, size);
4699  if ((int) strlen(line) + 1 < size)
4700  {
4701  strcat(line, "\n");
4702  }
4703  return status;
4704  }
4705  else
4706  {
4707  ASSERT(0);
4708  return false;
4709  }
4710 }
4711 
4712 static char *
4713 read_inline_file(struct in_src *is, const char *close_tag,
4714  int *num_lines, struct gc_arena *gc)
4715 {
4716  char line[OPTION_LINE_SIZE];
4717  struct buffer buf = alloc_buf(8*OPTION_LINE_SIZE);
4718  char *ret;
4719  bool endtagfound = false;
4720 
4721  while (in_src_get(is, line, sizeof(line)))
4722  {
4723  (*num_lines)++;
4724  char *line_ptr = line;
4725  /* Remove leading spaces */
4726  while (isspace(*line_ptr))
4727  {
4728  line_ptr++;
4729  }
4730  if (!strncmp(line_ptr, close_tag, strlen(close_tag)))
4731  {
4732  endtagfound = true;
4733  break;
4734  }
4735  if (!buf_safe(&buf, strlen(line)+1))
4736  {
4737  /* Increase buffer size */
4738  struct buffer buf2 = alloc_buf(buf.capacity * 2);
4739  ASSERT(buf_copy(&buf2, &buf));
4740  buf_clear(&buf);
4741  free_buf(&buf);
4742  buf = buf2;
4743  }
4744  buf_printf(&buf, "%s", line);
4745  }
4746  if (!endtagfound)
4747  {
4748  msg(M_FATAL, "ERROR: Endtag %s missing", close_tag);
4749  }
4750  ret = string_alloc(BSTR(&buf), gc);
4751  buf_clear(&buf);
4752  free_buf(&buf);
4753  secure_memzero(line, sizeof(line));
4754  return ret;
4755 }
4756 
4757 static int
4758 check_inline_file(struct in_src *is, char *p[], struct gc_arena *gc)
4759 {
4760  int num_inline_lines = 0;
4761 
4762  if (p[0] && !p[1])
4763  {
4764  char *arg = p[0];
4765  if (arg[0] == '<' && arg[strlen(arg)-1] == '>')
4766  {
4767  struct buffer close_tag;
4768 
4769  arg[strlen(arg) - 1] = '\0';
4770  p[0] = string_alloc(arg + 1, gc);
4771  close_tag = alloc_buf(strlen(p[0]) + 4);
4772  buf_printf(&close_tag, "</%s>", p[0]);
4773  p[1] = read_inline_file(is, BSTR(&close_tag), &num_inline_lines, gc);
4774  p[2] = NULL;
4775  free_buf(&close_tag);
4776  }
4777  }
4778  return num_inline_lines;
4779 }
4780 
4781 static int
4782 check_inline_file_via_fp(FILE *fp, char *p[], struct gc_arena *gc)
4783 {
4784  struct in_src is;
4785  is.type = IS_TYPE_FP;
4786  is.u.fp = fp;
4787  return check_inline_file(&is, p, gc);
4788 }
4789 
4790 static int
4791 check_inline_file_via_buf(struct buffer *multiline, char *p[],
4792  struct gc_arena *gc)
4793 {
4794  struct in_src is;
4795  is.type = IS_TYPE_BUF;
4796  is.u.multiline = multiline;
4797  return check_inline_file(&is, p, gc);
4798 }
