4800 static void
4801 add_option(struct options *options,
4802  char *p[],
4803  bool is_inline,
4804  const char *file,
4805  int line,
4806  const int level,
4807  const int msglevel,
4808  const unsigned int permission_mask,
4809  unsigned int *option_types_found,
4810  struct env_set *es);
4811 
4812 static void
4813 read_config_file(struct options *options,
4814  const char *file,
4815  int level,
4816  const char *top_file,
4817  const int top_line,
4818  const int msglevel,
4819  const unsigned int permission_mask,
4820  unsigned int *option_types_found,
4821  struct env_set *es)
4822 {
4823  const int max_recursive_levels = 10;
4824  FILE *fp;
4825  int line_num;
4826  char line[OPTION_LINE_SIZE+1];
4827  char *p[MAX_PARMS+1];
4828 
4829  ++level;
4830  if (level <= max_recursive_levels)
4831  {
4832  if (streq(file, "stdin"))
4833  {
4834  fp = stdin;
4835  }
4836  else
4837  {
4838  fp = platform_fopen(file, "r");
4839  }
4840  if (fp)
4841  {
4842  line_num = 0;
4843  while (fgets(line, sizeof(line), fp))
4844  {
4845  int offset = 0;
4846  CLEAR(p);
4847  ++line_num;
4848  if (strlen(line) == OPTION_LINE_SIZE)
4849  {
4850  msg(msglevel, "In %s:%d: Maximum option line length (%d) exceeded, line starts with %s",
4851  file, line_num, OPTION_LINE_SIZE, line);
4852  }
4853 
4854  /* Ignore UTF-8 BOM at start of stream */
4855  if (line_num == 1 && strncmp(line, "\xEF\xBB\xBF", 3) == 0)
4856  {
4857  offset = 3;
4858  }
4859  if (parse_line(line + offset, p, SIZE(p)-1, file, line_num, msglevel, &options->gc))
4860  {
4861  bypass_doubledash(&p[0]);
4862  int lines_inline = check_inline_file_via_fp(fp, p, &options->gc);
4863  add_option(options, p, lines_inline, file, line_num, level,
4864  msglevel, permission_mask, option_types_found,
4865  es);
4866  line_num += lines_inline;
4867  }
4868  }
4869  if (fp != stdin)
4870  {
4871  fclose(fp);
4872  }
4873  }
4874  else
4875  {
4876  msg(msglevel, "In %s:%d: Error opening configuration file: %s", top_file, top_line, file);
4877  }
4878  }
4879  else
4880  {
4881  msg(msglevel, "In %s:%d: Maximum recursive include levels exceeded in include attempt of file %s -- probably you have a configuration file that tries to include itself.", top_file, top_line, file);
4882  }
4883  secure_memzero(line, sizeof(line));
4884  CLEAR(p);
4885 }
4886 
4887 static void
4888 read_config_string(const char *prefix,
4889  struct options *options,
4890  const char *config,
4891  const int msglevel,
4892  const unsigned int permission_mask,
4893  unsigned int *option_types_found,
4894  struct env_set *es)
4895 {
4896  char line[OPTION_LINE_SIZE];
4897  struct buffer multiline;
4898  int line_num = 0;
4899 
4900  buf_set_read(&multiline, (uint8_t *)config, strlen(config));
4901 
4902  while (buf_parse(&multiline, '\n', line, sizeof(line)))
4903  {
4904  char *p[MAX_PARMS+1];
4905  CLEAR(p);
4906  ++line_num;
4907  if (parse_line(line, p, SIZE(p)-1, prefix, line_num, msglevel, &options->gc))
4908  {
4909  bypass_doubledash(&p[0]);
4910  int lines_inline = check_inline_file_via_buf(&multiline, p, &options->gc);
4911  add_option(options, p, lines_inline, prefix, line_num, 0, msglevel,
4912  permission_mask, option_types_found, es);
4913  line_num += lines_inline;
4914  }
4915  CLEAR(p);
4916  }
4917  secure_memzero(line, sizeof(line));
4918 }
4919 
4920 void
4921 parse_argv(struct options *options,
4922  const int argc,
4923  char *argv[],
4924  const int msglevel,
4925  const unsigned int permission_mask,
4926  unsigned int *option_types_found,
4927  struct env_set *es)
4928 {
4929  /* usage message */
4930  if (argc <= 1)
4931  {
4932  usage();
4933  }
4934 
4935  /* config filename specified only? */
4936  if (argc == 2 && strncmp(argv[1], "--", 2))
4937  {
4938  char *p[MAX_PARMS+1];
4939  CLEAR(p);
4940  p[0] = "config";
4941  p[1] = argv[1];
4942  add_option(options, p, false, NULL, 0, 0, msglevel, permission_mask,
4943  option_types_found, es);
4944  }
4945  else
4946  {
4947  /* parse command line */
4948  for (int i = 1; i < argc; ++i)
4949  {
4950  char *p[MAX_PARMS+1];
4951  CLEAR(p);
4952  p[0] = argv[i];
4953  if (strncmp(p[0], "--", 2))
4954  {
4955  msg(msglevel, "I'm trying to parse \"%s\" as an --option parameter but I don't see a leading '--'", p[0]);
4956  }
4957  else
4958  {
4959  p[0] += 2;
4960  }
4961 
4962  int j;
4963  for (j = 1; j < MAX_PARMS; ++j)
4964  {
4965  if (i + j < argc)
4966  {
4967  char *arg = argv[i + j];
4968  if (strncmp(arg, "--", 2))
4969  {
4970  p[j] = arg;
4971  }
4972  else
4973  {
4974  break;
4975  }
4976  }
4977  }
4978  add_option(options, p, false, NULL, 0, 0, msglevel, permission_mask,
4979  option_types_found, es);
4980  i += j - 1;
4981  }
4982  }
4983 }
4984 
4993 static bool
4994 apply_pull_filter(const struct options *o, char *line)
4995 {
4996  struct pull_filter *f;
4997 
4998  if (!o->pull_filter_list)
4999  {
5000  return true;
5001  }
5002 
5003  /* skip leading spaces matching the behaviour of parse_line */
5004  while (isspace(*line))
5005  {
5006  line++;
5007  }
5008 
5009  for (f = o->pull_filter_list->head; f; f = f->next)
5010  {
5011  if (f->type == PUF_TYPE_ACCEPT && strncmp(line, f->pattern, f->size) == 0)
5012  {
5013  msg(D_LOW, "Pushed option accepted by filter: '%s'", line);
5014  return true;
5015  }
5016  else if (f->type == PUF_TYPE_IGNORE && strncmp(line, f->pattern, f->size) == 0)
5017  {
5018  msg(D_PUSH, "Pushed option removed by filter: '%s'", line);
5019  *line = '\0';
5020  return true;
5021  }
5022  else if (f->type == PUF_TYPE_REJECT && strncmp(line, f->pattern, f->size) == 0)
5023  {
5024  msg(M_WARN, "Pushed option rejected by filter: '%s'. Restarting.", line);
5025  *line = '\0';
5026  throw_signal_soft(SIGUSR1, "Offending option received from server");
5027  return false;
5028  }
5029  }
5030  return true;
5031 }
5032 
5033 bool
5034 apply_push_options(struct options *options,
5035  struct buffer *buf,
5036  unsigned int permission_mask,
5037  unsigned int *option_types_found,
5038  struct env_set *es)
5039 {
5040  char line[OPTION_PARM_SIZE];
5041  int line_num = 0;
5042  const char *file = "[PUSH-OPTIONS]";
5043  const int msglevel = D_PUSH_ERRORS|M_OPTERR;
5044 
5045  while (buf_parse(buf, ',', line, sizeof(line)))
5046  {
5047  char *p[MAX_PARMS+1];
5048  CLEAR(p);
5049  ++line_num;
5050  if (!apply_pull_filter(options, line))
5051  {
5052  return false; /* Cause push/pull error and stop push processing */
5053  }
5054  if (parse_line(line, p, SIZE(p)-1, file, line_num, msglevel, &options->gc))
5055  {
5056  add_option(options, p, false, file, line_num, 0, msglevel,
5057  permission_mask, option_types_found, es);
5058  }
5059  }
5060  return true;
5061 }

5064 options_server_import(struct options *o,
5065  const char *filename,
5066  int msglevel,
5067  unsigned int permission_mask,
5068  unsigned int *option_types_found,
5069  struct env_set *es)
5070 {
5071  msg(D_PUSH, "OPTIONS IMPORT: reading client specific options from: %s", filename);
5072  read_config_file(o,
5073  filename,
5074  0,
5075  filename,
5076  0,
5077  msglevel,
5078  permission_mask,
5079  option_types_found,
5080  es);
5081 }

5083 void
5084 options_string_import(struct options *options,
5085  const char *config,
5086  const int msglevel,
5087  const unsigned int permission_mask,
5088  unsigned int *option_types_found,
5089  struct env_set *es)
5090 {
5091  read_config_string("[CONFIG-STRING]", options, config, msglevel, permission_mask, option_types_found, es);
5092 }
5093 
5094 #if P2MP
5095 
5096 #define VERIFY_PERMISSION(mask) { \
5097  if (!verify_permission(p[0], file, line, (mask), permission_mask, \
5098  option_types_found, msglevel, options, is_inline)) \
5099  { \
5100  goto err; \
5101  } \
5102 }
5103 
5104 static bool
5105 verify_permission(const char *name,
5106  const char *file,
5107  int line,
5108  const unsigned int type,
5109  const unsigned int allowed,
5110  unsigned int *found,
5111  const int msglevel,
5112  struct options *options,
5113  bool is_inline)
5114 {
5115  if (!(type & allowed))
5116  {
5117  msg(msglevel, "option '%s' cannot be used in this context (%s)", name, file);
5118  return false;
5119  }
5120 
5121  if (is_inline && !(type & OPT_P_INLINE))
5122  {
5123  msg(msglevel, "option '%s' is not expected to be inline (%s:%d)", name,
5124  file, line);
5125  return false;
5126  }
5127 
5128  if (found)
5129  {
5130  *found |= type;
5131  }
5132 
5133 #ifndef ENABLE_SMALL
5134  /* Check if this options is allowed in connection block,
5135  * but we are currently not in a connection block
5136  * unless this is a pushed option.
5137  * Parsing a connection block uses a temporary options struct without
5138  * connection_list
5139  */
5140 
5141  if ((type & OPT_P_CONNECTION) && options->connection_list
5142  && !(allowed & OPT_P_PULL_MODE))
5143  {
5144  if (file)
5145  {
5146  msg(M_WARN, "Option '%s' in %s:%d is ignored by previous <connection> blocks ", name, file, line);
5147  }
5148  else
5149  {
5150  msg(M_WARN, "Option '%s' is ignored by previous <connection> blocks", name);
5151  }
5152  }
5153 #endif
5154  return true;
5155 }
5156 
5157 #else /* if P2MP */
5158 
5159 #define VERIFY_PERMISSION(mask)
5160 
5161 #endif /* if P2MP */
5162 
5163 /*
5164  * Check that an option doesn't have too
5165  * many parameters.
5166  */
5167 
5168 #define NM_QUOTE_HINT (1<<0)
5169 
5170 static bool
5171 no_more_than_n_args(const int msglevel,
5172  char *p[],
5173  const int max,
5174  const unsigned int flags)
5175 {
5176  const int len = string_array_len((const char **)p);
5177 
5178  if (!len)
5179  {
5180  return false;
5181  }
5182 
5183  if (len > max)
5184  {
5185  msg(msglevel, "the --%s directive should have at most %d parameter%s.%s",
5186  p[0],
5187  max - 1,
5188  max >= 3 ? "s" : "",
5189  (flags & NM_QUOTE_HINT) ? " To pass a list of arguments as one of the parameters, try enclosing them in double quotes (\"\")." : "");
5190  return false;
5191  }
5192  else
5193  {
5194  return true;
5195  }
5196 }
5197 
5198 static inline int
5199 msglevel_forward_compatible(struct options *options, const int msglevel)
5200 {
5201  return options->forward_compatible ? M_WARN : msglevel;
5202 }
5203 
5204 static void
5205 set_user_script(struct options *options,
5206  const char **script,
5207  const char *new_script,
5208  const char *type,
5209  bool in_chroot)
5210 {
5211  if (*script)
5212  {
5213  msg(M_WARN, "Multiple --%s scripts defined. "
5214  "The previously configured script is overridden.", type);
5215  }
5216  *script = new_script;
5217  options->user_script_used = true;
5218 
5219 #ifndef ENABLE_SMALL
5220  {
5221  char script_name[100];
5222  openvpn_snprintf(script_name, sizeof(script_name),
5223  "--%s script", type);
5224 
5225  if (check_cmd_access(*script, script_name, (in_chroot ? options->chroot_dir : NULL)))
5226  {
5227  msg(M_USAGE, "Please correct this error.");
5228  }
5229 
5230  }
5231 #endif
5232 }

5234 #ifdef USE_COMP
5235 static void
5236 show_compression_warning(struct compress_options *info)
5237 {
5238  if (comp_non_stub_enabled(info))
5239  {
5240  /*
5241  * Check if already displayed the strong warning and enabled full
5242  * compression
5243  */
5244  if (!(info->flags & COMP_F_ALLOW_COMPRESS))
5245  {
5246  msg(M_WARN, "WARNING: Compression for receiving enabled. "
5247  "Compression has been used in the past to break encryption. "
5248  "Sent packets are not compressed unless \"allow-compression yes\" "
5249  "is also set.");
5250  }
5251  }
5252 }
5253 #endif
5254 
5255 static void
5256 add_option(struct options *options,
5257  char *p[],
5258  bool is_inline,
5259  const char *file,
5260  int line,
5261  const int level,
5262  const int msglevel,
5263  const unsigned int permission_mask,
5264  unsigned int *option_types_found,
5265  struct env_set *es)
5266 {
5267  struct gc_arena gc = gc_new();
5268  const bool pull_mode = BOOL_CAST(permission_mask & OPT_P_PULL_MODE);
5269  int msglevel_fc = msglevel_forward_compatible(options, msglevel);
5270 
5271  ASSERT(MAX_PARMS >= 7);
5272 
5273  /*
5274  * If directive begins with "setenv opt" prefix, don't raise an error if
5275  * directive is unrecognized.
5276  */
5277  if (streq(p[0], "setenv") && p[1] && streq(p[1], "opt") && !(permission_mask & OPT_P_PULL_MODE))
5278  {
5279  if (!p[2])
5280  {
5281  p[2] = "setenv opt"; /* will trigger an error that includes setenv opt */
5282  }
5283  p += 2;
5284  msglevel_fc = M_WARN;
5285  }
5286 
5287  if (!file)
5288  {
5289  file = "[CMD-LINE]";
5290  line = 1;
5291  }
5292  if (streq(p[0], "help"))
5293  {
5294  VERIFY_PERMISSION(OPT_P_GENERAL);
5295  usage();
5296  if (p[1])
5297  {
5298  msg(msglevel, "--help does not accept any parameters");
5299  goto err;
5300  }
5301  }
5302  if (streq(p[0], "version") && !p[1])
5303  {
5304  VERIFY_PERMISSION(OPT_P_GENERAL);
5305  usage_version();
5306  }
5307  else if (streq(p[0], "config") && p[1] && !p[2])
5308  {
5309  VERIFY_PERMISSION(OPT_P_CONFIG);
5310 
5311  /* save first config file only in options */
5312  if (!options->config)
5313  {
5314  options->config = p[1];
5315  }
5316 
5317  read_config_file(options, p[1], level, file, line, msglevel, permission_mask, option_types_found, es);
5318  }
5319 #if defined(ENABLE_DEBUG) && !defined(ENABLE_SMALL)
5320  else if (streq(p[0], "show-gateway") && !p[2])
5321  {
5322  struct route_gateway_info rgi;
5323  struct route_ipv6_gateway_info rgi6;
5324  struct in6_addr remote = IN6ADDR_ANY_INIT;
5325  openvpn_net_ctx_t net_ctx;
5326  VERIFY_PERMISSION(OPT_P_GENERAL);
5327  if (p[1])
5328  {
5329  get_ipv6_addr(p[1], &remote, NULL, M_WARN);
5330  }
5331  net_ctx_init(NULL, &net_ctx);
5332  get_default_gateway(&rgi, &net_ctx);
5333  get_default_gateway_ipv6(&rgi6, &remote, &net_ctx);
5334  print_default_gateway(M_INFO, &rgi, &rgi6);
5335  openvpn_exit(OPENVPN_EXIT_STATUS_GOOD); /* exit point */
5336  }
5337 #endif
5338 #if 0
5339  else if (streq(p[0], "foreign-option") && p[1])
5340  {
5341  VERIFY_PERMISSION(OPT_P_IPWIN32);
5342  foreign_option(options, p, 3, es);
5343  }
5344 #endif
5345  else if (streq(p[0], "echo") || streq(p[0], "parameter"))
5346  {
5347  struct buffer string = alloc_buf_gc(OPTION_PARM_SIZE, &gc);
5348  int j;
5349  bool good = true;
5350 
5351  VERIFY_PERMISSION(OPT_P_ECHO);
5352 
5353  for (j = 1; j < MAX_PARMS; ++j)
5354  {
5355  if (!p[j])
5356  {
5357  break;
5358  }
5359  if (j > 1)
5360  {
5361  good &= buf_printf(&string, " ");
5362  }
5363  good &= buf_printf(&string, "%s", p[j]);
5364  }
5365  if (good)
5366  {
5367  /* only message-related ECHO are logged, since other ECHOs
5368  * can potentially include security-sensitive strings */
5369  if (p[1] && strncmp(p[1], "msg", 3) == 0)
5370  {
5371  msg(M_INFO, "%s:%s",
5372  pull_mode ? "ECHO-PULL" : "ECHO",
5373  BSTR(&string));
5374  }
5375 #ifdef ENABLE_MANAGEMENT
5376  if (management)
5377  {
5378  management_echo(management, BSTR(&string), pull_mode);
5379  }
5380 #endif
5381  }
5382  else
5383  {
5384  msg(M_WARN, "echo/parameter option overflow");
5385  }
5386  }
5387 #ifdef ENABLE_MANAGEMENT
5388  else if (streq(p[0], "management") && p[1] && p[2] && !p[4])
5389  {
5390  VERIFY_PERMISSION(OPT_P_GENERAL);
5391  if (streq(p[2], "unix"))
5392  {
5393 #if UNIX_SOCK_SUPPORT
5394  options->management_flags |= MF_UNIX_SOCK;
5395 #else
5396  msg(msglevel, "MANAGEMENT: this platform does not support unix domain sockets");
5397  goto err;
5398 #endif
5399  }
5400 
5401  options->management_addr = p[1];
5402  options->management_port = p[2];
5403  if (p[3])
5404  {
5405  options->management_user_pass = p[3];
5406  }
5407  }
5408  else if (streq(p[0], "management-client-user") && p[1] && !p[2])
5409  {
5410  VERIFY_PERMISSION(OPT_P_GENERAL);
5411  options->management_client_user = p[1];
5412  }
5413  else if (streq(p[0], "management-client-group") && p[1] && !p[2])
5414  {
5415  VERIFY_PERMISSION(OPT_P_GENERAL);
5416  options->management_client_group = p[1];
5417  }
5418  else if (streq(p[0], "management-query-passwords") && !p[1])
5419  {
5420  VERIFY_PERMISSION(OPT_P_GENERAL);
5421  options->management_flags |= MF_QUERY_PASSWORDS;
5422  }
5423  else if (streq(p[0], "management-query-remote") && !p[1])
5424  {
5425  VERIFY_PERMISSION(OPT_P_GENERAL);
5426  options->management_flags |= MF_QUERY_REMOTE;
5427  }
5428  else if (streq(p[0], "management-query-proxy") && !p[1])
5429  {
5430  VERIFY_PERMISSION(OPT_P_GENERAL);
5431  options->management_flags |= MF_QUERY_PROXY;
5432  }
5433  else if (streq(p[0], "management-hold") && !p[1])
5434  {
5435  VERIFY_PERMISSION(OPT_P_GENERAL);
5436  options->management_flags |= MF_HOLD;
5437  }
5438  else if (streq(p[0], "management-signal") && !p[1])
5439  {
5440  VERIFY_PERMISSION(OPT_P_GENERAL);
5441  options->management_flags |= MF_SIGNAL;
5442  }
5443  else if (streq(p[0], "management-forget-disconnect") && !p[1])
5444  {
5445  VERIFY_PERMISSION(OPT_P_GENERAL);
5446  options->management_flags |= MF_FORGET_DISCONNECT;
5447  }
5448  else if (streq(p[0], "management-up-down") && !p[1])
5449  {
5450  VERIFY_PERMISSION(OPT_P_GENERAL);
5451  options->management_flags |= MF_UP_DOWN;
5452  }
5453  else if (streq(p[0], "management-client") && !p[2])
5454  {
5455  VERIFY_PERMISSION(OPT_P_GENERAL);
5456  options->management_flags |= MF_CONNECT_AS_CLIENT;
5457  options->management_write_peer_info_file = p[1];
5458  }
5459 #ifdef ENABLE_MANAGEMENT
5460  else if (streq(p[0], "management-external-key"))
5461  {
5462  VERIFY_PERMISSION(OPT_P_GENERAL);
5463  for (int j = 1; j < MAX_PARMS && p[j] != NULL; ++j)
5464  {
5465  if (streq(p[j], "nopadding"))
5466  {
5467  options->management_flags |= MF_EXTERNAL_KEY_NOPADDING;
5468  }
5469  else if (streq(p[j], "pkcs1"))
5470  {
5471  options->management_flags |= MF_EXTERNAL_KEY_PKCS1PAD;
5472  }
5473  else
5474  {
5475  msg(msglevel, "Unknown management-external-key flag: %s", p[j]);
5476  }
5477  }
5478  /*
5479  * When no option is present, assume that only PKCS1
5480  * padding is supported
5481  */
5482  if (!(options->management_flags
5483  &(MF_EXTERNAL_KEY_NOPADDING | MF_EXTERNAL_KEY_PKCS1PAD)))
5484  {
5485  options->management_flags |= MF_EXTERNAL_KEY_PKCS1PAD;
5486  }
5487  options->management_flags |= MF_EXTERNAL_KEY;
5488  }
5489  else if (streq(p[0], "management-external-cert") && p[1] && !p[2])
5490  {
5491  VERIFY_PERMISSION(OPT_P_GENERAL);
5492  options->management_flags |= MF_EXTERNAL_CERT;

6436  }

7286  goto err;
7287  }
7288  }

7305  goto err;
7306  }

7312 
7313  VERIFY_PERMISSION(OPT_P_INSTANCE);

7318  goto err;
7319  }

7326  goto err;

7482

7504  {
7505  int offset = atoi(p[2]);
7506

7525  goto err;

7582  }

7613  {

7615  }

7797  else if (streq(p[1], "yes"))

7799  msg(M_WARN, "WARNING: Compression for sending and receiving enabled. Compression has "

7802  "strongly discouraged for common usage. See --compress in the manual "
7803  "page for more information ");
7804 
7805  options->comp.flags |= COMP_F_ALLOW_COMPRESS;
7806  }
7807  else
7808  {
7809  msg(msglevel, "bad allow-compression option: %s -- "
7810  "must be 'yes', 'no', or 'asym'", p[1]);
7811  goto err;
7812  }
7813  }
7814  else if (streq(p[0], "comp-lzo") && !p[2])
7815  {
7816  VERIFY_PERMISSION(OPT_P_COMP);
7817 
7818  /* All lzo variants do not use swap */
7819  options->comp.flags &= ~COMP_F_SWAP;
7820 #if defined(ENABLE_LZO)
7821  if (p[1] && streq(p[1], "no"))

7825  options->comp.flags &= ~COMP_F_ADAPTIVE;
7826  }
7827 #if defined(ENABLE_LZO)

7829  {

7831  msg(msglevel, "Cannot set comp-lzo to '%s', "

7833  goto err;
7834  }

7838  {

7845  options->comp.flags |= COMP_F_ADAPTIVE;
7846  }
7847  else

7850  goto err;
7851  }
7852  }
7853  else

7855  options->comp.alg = COMP_ALG_LZO;
7856  options->comp.flags |= COMP_F_ADAPTIVE;
7857  }
